1
00:02:29,289 --> 00:02:32,334
<i>进来
Come in.</i>

2
00:02:32,668 --> 00:02:35,087
斯班塞先生
很抱歉打扰你
Mr Spencer.
Mr Spencer, I hate to bother you...

3
00:02:35,295 --> 00:02:37,756
有两个男人来过
but I thought you'd like to know
there were two men here.

4
00:02:37,965 --> 00:02:39,758
说是找你的
Two men askin' for you.

5
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:42,719
一个年轻人
另一个老些
A young man and a kind of older man.

6
00:02:42,928 --> 00:02:45,722
我说你不在
他们好像不高兴
They was sorry you wasn't in.
I said you wasn't.

7
00:02:45,931 --> 00:02:50,060
-他们有说会再来吗?
-没说但我想他们会再来的
- Did they say they'd be back?
- They didn't say, but I think they will.

8
00:02:50,269 --> 00:02:54,231
刚才我出去买东西的时候
看见他们在拐角那里等著
Just now, when I had to go to the store,
I seen them standing there at the corner.

9
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,650
也许我应该让他们进来
但不能打扰你
Maybe I shoulda let them in,
only you said not to disturb you -

10
00:02:56,859 --> 00:03:00,571
-是吗?
-我觉得他们会再来的
- Yes.
- And I'm sure They'll be back.

11
00:03:01,179 --> 00:03:03,974
你样子看上去很疲惫啊
You look kinda tired to me,
and that's a fact.

12
00:03:04,182 --> 00:03:06,309
有些头疼吗?
You got a headache or somethin'?

13
00:03:06,518 --> 00:03:09,938
我想你应该好好休息一下了
I think maybe you need a real rest.
That's what I think.

14
00:03:10,146 --> 00:03:13,859
斯班塞先生
你不该把钱到处放
Why, Mr Spencer. You oughtn't to leave
all that money lying around like that.

15
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:16,570
看到这样我觉得很不自然
Oh, it makes me nervous
to see money lying around.

16
00:03:16,778 --> 00:03:18,780
世界上不是
所有人都是诚实的
Everybody in the world
ain't honest, you know.

17
00:03:18,989 --> 00:03:21,241
但你可以相信我
我是很诚实的
Though I must say I haven't had
much trouble that way.

18
00:03:21,449 --> 00:03:25,912
<i>你的一些朋友打电话来了
还叫我不要告诉你
Those friends of yours
told me not to mention they'd called.</i>

19
00:03:26,121 --> 00:03:29,541
说想给你一个惊喜
但我还是要说一声
Wanted to surprise you. But I thought
you'd like to know somehow.

20
00:03:29,749 --> 00:03:32,419
是啊当然了如果他们
再来就让他们进来吧
Yes, yes. Of course. If they come back,
you may show them in.

21
00:03:32,586 --> 00:03:35,964
有一位叫马丁太太的人
很有意思
Yes. You know, Mrs Martin,
it's very funny.

22
00:03:36,173 --> 00:03:39,384
他们并不是我的朋友
还没见过我
They aren't exactly friends of mine.
They've never seen me.

23
00:03:39,593 --> 00:03:42,596
-很奇怪是吧?
-的确很奇怪
- That's odd, isn't it?
- 'Tis odd, like you say.

24
00:03:42,804 --> 00:03:47,559
既然我在这里
我就要见他们
And now that I'm here,
I'll have to meet them.

25
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:51,688
甚至要出去见他们
I may even go out and meet them.

26
00:03:51,897 --> 00:03:55,066
但现在还不是时候
And then again, I may not. Not yet.

27
00:03:55,275 --> 00:03:59,571
你继续睡吧
我把窗布拉下来
You go ahead with your nap.
I'll pull down the blind.

28
00:04:33,222 --> 00:04:36,392
<i>你们知道什麽?
你们只是在作势
What do you know?
You're bluffing. You've nothing on me.</i>

29
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:35,302
邮局吗?
我要发一封电报...
Hello, Postal Union?
I want to send a telegram

30
00:06:35,469 --> 00:06:39,640
给加州圣罗莎的
约瑟夫.牛顿
to Mrs Joseph Newton
in Santa Rosa, California.

31
00:06:39,849 --> 00:06:42,268
下面是内容
准备好了吗?
Here's the message. Ready?

32
00:06:42,476 --> 00:06:45,646
很想念你们句号
Lonesome for you all. Stop.

33
00:06:45,855 --> 00:06:49,233
我就来找你们句号
Am coming out to stay
with you awhile. Stop.

34
00:06:49,442 --> 00:06:52,611
周四到达
请来接我
Will arrive Thursday and try and stop me.

35
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:55,614
准确时间稍後告知
Will wire exact time later.

36
00:06:55,823 --> 00:06:57,908
祝福所有人...
Love to you all...

37
00:06:58,117 --> 00:07:02,455
并附上查利叔叔的吻
给小查莉
and a kiss for little Charlie
from her Uncle Charlie.

38
00:07:02,663 --> 00:07:06,917
没错签名就是查利叔叔
That's right. That's the signature.
"Uncle Charlie. "

39
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:09,086
是的圣罗莎
That's right. Santa Rosa.

40
00:07:11,797 --> 00:07:13,215
<i>加州圣罗莎
Santa Rosa, California.</i>

41
00:07:51,712 --> 00:07:56,133
<i>安妮听电话啊
Ann! Answer the telephone.</i>

42
00:08:17,988 --> 00:08:20,700
这里是牛顿家
Newton's residence.
Ann Newton speaking.

43
00:08:20,908 --> 00:08:24,704
噢你好汉德森太太
我是安妮
Oh, hello, Mrs Henderson. This is Ann.

44
00:08:24,912 --> 00:08:27,164
妈妈还没回家
Mother isn't home yet.

45
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:30,751
电报?我...
A telegram? Well...

46
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,879
我找不到铅笔
还是等她回来吧
I don't see a pencil, so maybe
she better call you back.

47
00:08:34,088 --> 00:08:37,216
我正努力使自己
专注一些...
I'm trying to keep my mind free of things
that don't matter...

48
00:08:37,425 --> 00:08:40,678
因为我在思考许多问题
because I have so much
to keep on my mind.

49
00:08:40,886 --> 00:08:42,930
数不清的问题
Innumerable things.

50
00:08:43,139 --> 00:08:46,392
我会告诉她回电的
谢谢你
I'll have her call back.
Thank you for calling.

51
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,477
再见
Goodbye.

52
00:08:53,691 --> 00:08:55,693
安妮你妈妈呢?
Hello, Ann. Where's your mother?

53
00:08:55,901 --> 00:08:57,695
<i>-她出去了
-出去了?
- She ' s out.
- Out?</i>

54
00:08:57,903 --> 00:09:00,906
邮局的汉德森太太
刚刚打电话来的
Mrs Henderson just called
from the Postal Union Office.

55
00:09:01,115 --> 00:09:02,908
她说我们收到一封电报
She says we have a telegram.

56
00:09:03,117 --> 00:09:06,412
我本可以记下来的
但我找不到铅笔
I would have taken it down,
only I couldn't find a pencil. I looked.

57
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,748
电报吗?
Telegram, eh?

58
00:09:08,956 --> 00:09:14,003
我说过你们的萨拉阿姨
如果领到执照就有麻烦了
I knew there'd be trouble if
your Aunt Sarah got her driver's licence.

59
00:09:14,211 --> 00:09:16,714
<i>-事故地点在哪里?
-我没有记下来
- Whereabouts was the accident?
- I didn't take notes.</i>

60
00:09:16,922 --> 00:09:19,508
噢那麽来一个吻好吗?
Oh. Then how about a kiss?

61
00:09:24,221 --> 00:09:27,266
那不是很有趣吗?
我是家里最特别的女孩...
Isn't that the funniest thing?
Here I am, practically a child

62
00:09:27,475 --> 00:09:29,393
看一些你们都不看的书
and I wouldn't read the things you read.

63
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:32,104
我想那些书
会给你带来恶梦的
Mm-hm. Well, I guess
they'd give you bad dreams.

64
00:09:32,313 --> 00:09:36,275
恶梦?爸爸你不明白
那些传说和神话...
Bad dreams? You don't understand, Papa.
Mystery stories have done -

65
00:09:36,484 --> 00:09:38,486
-罗杰呢?
-出去了还有人类的思想...
- Where's Roger?
- Out. The average mind -

66
00:09:38,694 --> 00:09:42,531
-查莉呢?
-她在房间里思考
- Where's Charlie?
- Out. No, she's in her room thinking.

67
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:45,868
别看太多了
对你的眼睛不好
Well, don't read too much.
You'll ruin your eyes.

68
00:09:46,077 --> 00:09:48,871
别看我的书了
你在看什麽?
And leave my book alone.
What's that you're reading?

69
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:52,124
<i>-艾凡赫
-噢
- Ivanhoe.
- Hm? Oh.</i>

70
00:09:58,339 --> 00:10:01,217
-是谁?
-是我
- Who is it?
- It's me.

71
00:10:05,596 --> 00:10:07,640
怎麽了?
不舒服吗?
What's the matter?
Don't you feel well?

72
00:10:07,848 --> 00:10:10,101
不我很好
No. I'm perfectly well.

73
00:10:10,309 --> 00:10:14,980
我已经想了很久
然後得出结论我应该放弃
I've just been thinking for hours,
and I've come to the conclusion I give up.

74
00:10:15,189 --> 00:10:17,441
<i>-只能放弃
-你要放弃什麽?
- I simply give up.
- What are you going to give up?</i>

75
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:21,404
你认为家庭应该是
世界上最美好的事物吗?
Have you ever to thought that a family
should be the most wonderful thing ever?

76
00:10:21,612 --> 00:10:23,989
而我们的家庭正趋向分解
And that this family's
just gone to pieces?

77
00:10:24,198 --> 00:10:27,034
-是吗?
-当然是了
- We have?
- Of course we have.

78
00:10:27,243 --> 00:10:32,415
我们只是惯例地生活下去
那种惯例太可怕了
We just sort of go along and
nothing happens. We're in a terrible rut.

79
00:10:32,623 --> 00:10:36,836
几个月前我已经在想了
我们的将来会是怎样?
It's been on my mind for months.
What's going to be our future?

80
00:10:37,044 --> 00:10:40,256
噢查莉别这样
事情不是那麽糟糕的
Oh, come now, Charlie.
Things aren't as bad as that.

81
00:10:40,464 --> 00:10:43,676
-银行一月份已经
给我加薪了   -钱
- The bank gave me a raise last January.
- Money.

82
00:10:43,884 --> 00:10:47,680
在我说心灵的时候
你怎麽可以说到钱呢?
How can you talk about money
when I'm talking about souls?

83
00:10:47,888 --> 00:10:50,725
我们一起吃饭然後睡觉
We eat and sleep and that's about all.

84
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,060
并没有真正的交流
We don't even have
any real conversations.

85
00:10:53,269 --> 00:10:55,396
<i>我们只是说话
还有工作
- We just talk.
- And work.</i>

86
00:10:55,604 --> 00:10:58,899
可怜的妈妈
那麽辛苦地工作
Yes. Poor Mother. She works like a dog.

87
00:10:59,108 --> 00:11:01,986
<i>-就像一个佣人
-她在哪里?
- Just like a dog.
- Where is she?</i>

88
00:11:02,194 --> 00:11:06,032
她出去了
她回来了也是一样地工作
She's out. When she comes back,
it'll be the same thing.

89
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:11,370
做晚餐洗碗然後睡觉
我不明白她怎麽可以忍受
Dinner, then dishes, then bed.
I don't see how she stands it.

90
00:11:12,788 --> 00:11:14,957
你知道她是一个很好的女人
You know,
she's really a wonderful woman.

91
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:19,545
她不仅仅是一个母亲
我们应该为她做些事情
I mean, she's not just a mother. And
I think we ought to do something for her.

92
00:11:19,754 --> 00:11:23,215
<i>-你觉得应该吗?
-应该那你认为要做些什麽呢?
- Don ' t you think we should?
- Yeah. What were you thinking of?</i>

93
00:11:23,424 --> 00:11:27,678
噢我想不出什麽
Oh, nothing, I suppose.

94
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:30,056
我想我们只能等待
奇迹出现了
I guess we'll just have to wait
for a miracle or something.

95
00:11:30,264 --> 00:11:33,225
噢查莉你说得对
Oh, now, Charlie, you're right.
Absolutely right.

96
00:11:33,434 --> 00:11:38,147
-我会想办法...
-噢我不再相信什麽好意愿了
- I'll figure out some way -
- I don't believe in good intentions now.

97
00:11:38,355 --> 00:11:41,901
-我现在只是等待著奇迹
-噢查莉
- All I'm waiting for now is a miracle.
- Oh, Charlie.

98
00:11:42,109 --> 00:11:44,153
後楼梯真陡啊
Those back stairs are steep.

99
00:11:44,361 --> 00:11:46,906
怎麽了查莉?
怎麽了祖?
What's the matter, Charlie?
What's the matter, Joe?

100
00:11:47,114 --> 00:11:51,243
-看来...
-噢我成了唠叨的老太婆了
- Well, it seems that, uh -
- Oh, I've become a nagging old maid.

101
00:11:51,452 --> 00:11:54,580
这帽子你答应会扔掉的
但你还戴著它进城里
You went downtown in that awful old
hat you'd promised you'd throw away.

102
00:11:54,789 --> 00:11:57,833
<i>-妈妈
-亲爱的我戴什麽
帽子有什麽紧要吗?
- Mama.
- Darling, does it matter what hat I wear?</i>

103
00:11:58,042 --> 00:12:01,670
<i>-妈妈
-妈妈你怎麽让
自己的孩子这样向你大喊呢?
- Mama.
- Why do you let that child yell at you?</i>

104
00:12:01,879 --> 00:12:04,423
-如果她...
-我反正都要下去的
- If she -
- I'm going downstairs, anyway.

105
00:12:04,632 --> 00:12:07,343
<i>祖我进来的时候
你们在谈什麽呢?
Joe, what were you
both talking about when I came in?</i>

106
00:12:07,551 --> 00:12:09,345
<i>谈奇迹的事情
Something about a miracle.</i>

107
00:12:09,553 --> 00:12:11,931
<i>没什麽的
查莉只是心情不太好
Oh, it's nothing.
Charlie ' s a bit under the weather.</i>

108
00:12:12,139 --> 00:12:13,974
<i>她很快就会没事的
Oh. Well, she ' II be all right.</i>

109
00:12:14,183 --> 00:12:17,812
<i>好了亲爱的快下去吧
不要站在这里
Well, come on, dear. Let's go
downstairs. No use standing here.</i>

110
00:12:18,062 --> 00:12:20,648
我去喝一瓶啤酒
I'm going to get myself a bottle of beer.

111
00:12:20,856 --> 00:12:22,733
妈妈
我要去发一封电报
Mother, I'm going downtown
and send a telegram.

112
00:12:22,942 --> 00:12:25,111
为什麽
你要发电报给谁?
Why, darling, who do you know
to send a telegram to?

113
00:12:25,319 --> 00:12:28,823
我知道谁可以来拯救我们
I know a wonderful person who'll come
and stir us up. Just the one to save us.

114
00:12:29,031 --> 00:12:31,158
拯救我们?
What do you mean, "save us"?

115
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:34,328
现在就只有一个人可以做到
All this time, there's been
one right person to save us.

116
00:12:34,537 --> 00:12:38,666
-妈妈查理叔叔的地址是什麽?
-查理叔叔?
- What's Uncle Charlie's address?
- Uncle Charlie?

117
00:12:38,874 --> 00:12:41,460
-你不是去问他要钱吧?
-当然不是了
- You're not going to ask him for money?
- Of course not.

118
00:12:41,669 --> 00:12:44,422
那对我们没帮助地址呢?
上次我放在...
That wouldn't help us.
What's his address?

119
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:47,466
你们知道从药房那里...
- The last address I had -
- Do you know how many steps it is

120
00:12:47,675 --> 00:12:49,385
走回家要走多少步呢?
to get from here
to the drugstore and back?

121
00:12:49,593 --> 00:12:53,973
- 649.
-如果你忘记了, 我就不告诉你
- 649.
- If you've forgotten, I won't tell you.

122
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:56,851
-我记起来了是费城
- I remember. Philadelphia.

123
00:12:57,059 --> 00:13:00,813
-你不能无缘无故地叫一个大忙人过来啊
You can't ask a busy man
to come all this way for nothing.

124
00:13:01,021 --> 00:13:03,232
他会来的, 我的名字是因他而起的
He'll come for me. I'm named after him.

125
00:13:03,441 --> 00:13:05,818
此外, 我们是他唯一的亲戚
Besides, we're the only relatives
he has in the world.

126
00:13:06,026 --> 00:13:08,988
<i>如果从第四街走回来, 就是802步
If you come all the way up Fourth Street, it's 802.</i>

127
00:13:09,196 --> 00:13:11,282
-妈妈你猜猜?
-我没时间去猜
- Mama, guess what?
- I have no time for guessing.

128
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:13,409
你头发上面的是什麽?
What's that thing in your hair?

129
00:13:13,617 --> 00:13:17,747
我要告诉你的
要猜的话有趣一点
Well, I'll tell you anyway, even though
I think it's nicer when people guess.

130
00:13:17,955 --> 00:13:21,959
汉德森太太叫你打电话
给邮局我们有一封电报
Mrs Henderson said to call her at
the telegraph office. We have a telegram.

131
00:13:22,168 --> 00:13:24,378
安妮你不应该
把东西放在耳朵後面的
Ann, I don't think you ought to put things
behind your ears.

132
00:13:24,587 --> 00:13:28,507
-会进耳朵里面的
-艾玛安妮说我们有电报
- Something might get into your ear.
- Emmy, Ann says we have a telegram.

133
00:13:28,716 --> 00:13:32,136
我想你应该去查清楚
可能有人病了
I think you ought to find out about it.
Somebody might be sick or something.

134
00:13:32,344 --> 00:13:36,599
-汉德森太太没有读出来...
因为我找不到铅笔
Mrs Henderson didn't read the telegram
because I couldn't find a pencil.

135
00:13:36,807 --> 00:13:39,727
等我有了屋子之後
我会在周围放满铅笔
When I have a house, it's going
to be full of well-sharpened pencils.

136
00:13:39,935 --> 00:13:43,689
-汉德森太太有说是哪里来的电报吗?
-没有
- Did Mrs Henderson say who it's from?
- No, she didn't.

137
00:13:43,898 --> 00:13:46,567
她应该说电报从哪里来的
She might have said who it was from.

138
00:13:46,776 --> 00:13:49,236
-安妮那是我的椅子啊
-我会问清楚的
Come on, Ann. That's my chair.
I'll call up and find out.

139
00:13:49,445 --> 00:13:52,782
你们静一会好吗
If you will be quiet just a second.

140
00:13:54,492 --> 00:13:58,079
你好请接181好吗?
Hello. 181, please. I wonder who it can be?

141
00:13:58,287 --> 00:14:01,165
没什麽就是181
Oh, nothing, Operator. Just 181.

142
00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:03,876
<i>-如果是我姐姐的...
-喂?
- If that's from my sister -
- Hello?</i>

143
00:14:04,085 --> 00:14:06,921
汉德森太太吗?
我是艾玛
Mrs Henderson? This is Emma Newton.

144
00:14:07,129 --> 00:14:09,507
安妮说我有一封电报
Ann says you have a telegram for me.

145
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:11,509
妈妈你不用那麽大声的
- Mama, you don't have to shout.
- Ssh.

146
00:14:11,717 --> 00:14:14,970
爸爸妈妈
好像没用过电话一样
Really, Papa. You'd think
Mama had never seen a phone.

147
00:14:15,179 --> 00:14:17,098
她这样很不科学
She makes no allowance for science.

148
00:14:17,306 --> 00:14:20,226
认为用声音
就可以压倒听众
She thinks she has to cover the distance
by sheer lungpower.

149
00:14:20,434 --> 00:14:24,397
真好啊是周四吗?
Why, how wonderful. Thursday, you say?

150
00:14:24,605 --> 00:14:26,399
似乎有人就要来了
Looks like somebody's coming.

151
00:14:26,607 --> 00:14:30,403
-谁要来啊妈妈?
-那真是最大的惊喜啊
- Who's coming, Ma?
- Well, it's the most wonderful surprise.

152
00:14:30,611 --> 00:14:34,532
是我的弟弟就是他
It's my brother, you know.
My younger brother. The baby.

153
00:14:34,740 --> 00:14:38,411
是啊他被宠坏了家里
最小的一个总会被宠坏的
Yes, of course, a little spoiled.
Families always spoil the youngest.

154
00:14:39,662 --> 00:14:42,623
<i>这真是太好了
Well, it's just simply wonderful.</i>

155
00:14:42,832 --> 00:14:45,668
谢谢你汉德森太太
Thanks most awfully, Mrs Henderson.

156
00:14:46,836 --> 00:14:48,879
好了
Well...

157
00:14:50,047 --> 00:14:53,426
你猜是谁?
查理就要来了
What do you think? Charles is coming.

158
00:14:53,634 --> 00:14:55,428
-谁?
-你们的查理叔叔
- Who?
- Your Uncle Charlie.

159
00:14:55,636 --> 00:14:57,763
-查理叔叔?
Did you say "Charles"?

160
00:14:57,972 --> 00:15:03,769
-我们的查莉正去给他发电报呢
-她为什麽那样做呢?
And our Charlie's sending him a telegram.
Now, what made her think to do that?

161
00:15:03,978 --> 00:15:06,063
<i>你好啊查莉
你妈妈刚打电话来了
Hello, Charlie. I just called your house.</i>

162
00:15:06,272 --> 00:15:08,774
-你妈妈的电报
-是吗?
- Telegram for your mother.
- Did you?

163
00:15:08,983 --> 00:15:10,943
本来让比尔送过去的
你现在可以拿走了
Gonna send that by Bill Forest,
but you can take it.

164
00:15:11,152 --> 00:15:13,904
-谢谢
-是你叔叔的
Thanks. From your uncle.
The spoiled one.

165
00:15:14,113 --> 00:15:15,948
我叔叔?
查理叔叔?
My uncle? My Uncle Charlie?

166
00:15:16,157 --> 00:15:18,284
是的
Yeah.

167
00:15:22,621 --> 00:15:25,541
汉德森太太
你相信心灵感应吗?
Mrs Henderson,
do you believe in telepathy?

168
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,501
噢那是我的工作啊
Well, I ought to. That's my business.

169
00:15:27,710 --> 00:15:30,880
不是邮件
是心灵感应啊
Oh, not telegraphy. Mental telepathy.

170
00:15:31,088 --> 00:15:33,924
那就是说...
你想到了一些事情
Like...
well, suppose you have a thought,

171
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,802
假设你想到了一个
和你很相似的人
and suppose the thought's about
someone you're in tune with.

172
00:15:37,011 --> 00:15:41,265
然後那个与你
相隔千里的人回应你
Then across miles, that person knows
what you're thinking and answers you.

173
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:44,769
-就是心灵感应
-我不知道你在说什麽
- And it's all mental.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

174
00:15:44,977 --> 00:15:47,146
我只会收发邮件
I only send telegrams the normal way.

175
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:58,199
他听见我的
He heard me. He heard me.

176
00:16:11,545 --> 00:16:13,964
<i>-奥提斯先生?
-什麽?
- Mr Otis? Mr Otis?
- Yes?</i>

177
00:16:14,173 --> 00:16:17,510
就到圣罗莎了
你应该准备一下
You're almost in Santa Rosa. Want to be
ready when you get into Santa Rosa.

178
00:16:17,718 --> 00:16:21,514
<i>-我准备好了谢谢
-那我帮你拿行李出来
- I'm ready now. Thanks.
- Then I'll get all your bags out for you.</i>

179
00:16:21,722 --> 00:16:24,141
<i>-你觉得怎麽了
奥提斯先生?-很好
- How you feelin', Mr Otis?
- Pretty well.</i>

180
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,852
<i>只是有点虚弱
其他都很好
A little weak
but pretty well on the whole.</i>

181
00:16:27,061 --> 00:16:28,854
哦
Mm-hm.

182
00:16:29,063 --> 00:16:31,023
哈里告诉他你是医生吧
Harry, tell the porter you're a doctor.

183
00:16:31,232 --> 00:16:34,360
看看他有什麽问题
你也许可以帮他的
Ask if there's anything you can do.
Maybe you can help that poor soul.

184
00:16:34,568 --> 00:16:38,072
我正在休假啊搬运工
我丈夫是医生你去问问他...
- I'm on my vacation.
- My husband's a doctor and if there's -

185
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:41,617
不必了夫人
他不想见任何人
No, Ma'am. He's a very sick man.
Won't see anyone.

186
00:16:41,826 --> 00:16:44,745
我们上车之後就没见他出来
I haven't set eyes on him myself
since we first got on the train.

187
00:16:44,954 --> 00:16:47,456
<i>你脸色也不太好啊
Well, you don ' t look very well either.</i>

188
00:16:57,216 --> 00:17:00,302
到了孩子们出来吧
Ah, here we are. Come on, children.

189
00:17:00,511 --> 00:17:03,180
把门关好对了
Close the door, there. That's right.

190
00:18:04,116 --> 00:18:07,119
-你就是...
-查理
- Oh, are you -
- Charlie. Young Charlie.

191
00:18:07,328 --> 00:18:09,705
小查莉我开始
还认不出来呢我以为你病了
At first, I didn't know you.
I thought you were sick.

192
00:18:09,914 --> 00:18:11,582
-病了?
-你没病的
- Sick?
- You aren't sick, are you?

193
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:13,834
爸爸他在这里!
Look, Pop! Here he is!

194
00:18:14,043 --> 00:18:17,296
查理叔叔你没病啊
真有点奇怪
Why, Uncle Charlie, you're not sick.
That was the funniest thing.

195
00:18:17,505 --> 00:18:22,343
-我病了?祖你好啊
-你好查理
- Me, sick? Well, Joe, how are you?
- Alright, Charles.

196
00:18:22,551 --> 00:18:25,596
你们好啊罗杰安妮
应该认不出我了
Roger. Hello, Ann.
I bet you don't remember me.

197
00:18:25,805 --> 00:18:29,141
我隐约记起
你样子好像不同了
I remember you sort of.
You look different.

198
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:32,019
我们赶快回去吧
艾玛就做好晚餐了
Well, we better get started.
Emma's got the dinner almost ready.

199
00:18:32,186 --> 00:18:35,314
她不能来车站
晚餐第一啊
I couldn't persuade her to come
to the station. Dinner came first.

200
00:18:35,523 --> 00:18:38,317
-罗杰拿行李我来吧查理
-谢谢祖
- Roger, get the bags. I'll take that.
- Thank you, Joe.

201
00:18:38,526 --> 00:18:41,112
到了来吧
That's it. Come on. Let's go.

202
00:19:04,719 --> 00:19:06,721
<i>罗杰
拿这些行李
Come on, Roger, get these bags.</i>

203
00:19:08,514 --> 00:19:10,641
噢对你来说真的不重吗?
You, uh, sure that isn't
too heavy for you?

204
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:13,853
没什麽
我喜欢搬东西的
Oh, no. It's nothing. I love to carry.

205
00:19:17,565 --> 00:19:19,358
艾玛别动
Emma. Don't move.

206
00:19:19,567 --> 00:19:21,694
站在那里
你不像是艾玛.牛顿
Standing there,
you don't look like Emma Newton.

207
00:19:21,902 --> 00:19:25,698
你还是艾玛.奥克里
住在明尼苏达州
圣保罗市本翰大街46号
You look like Emma Spencer Oakley of
46 Burnham Street, St Paul, Minnesota.

208
00:19:25,906 --> 00:19:28,492
-那一区最漂亮的女孩!
-查理
- The prettiest girl on the block.
- Charles.

209
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:32,079
查莉妈妈车站里
只有叔叔一个人下车
Mama, nobody got off the train
but Uncle Charlie.

210
00:19:32,288 --> 00:19:34,623
-让我看看你
-只有我们在那里接人
- Let me look at you.
- There was only us meeting somebody.

211
00:19:34,832 --> 00:19:38,044
很难想像你会来这里
- To think you could take the time off.
- There was only one bed made up.

212
00:19:38,252 --> 00:19:41,756
-噢查理你来了真好
-艾玛别哭啊
- It's so wonderful to have you here.
- Emmy, Emmy, don't cry.

213
00:19:41,964 --> 00:19:44,300
你在想起
本翰大街46号吧
And imagine your thinking
of 46 Burnham Street.

214
00:19:44,508 --> 00:19:46,719
我很多年没想过那里了
I haven't thought of that
funny old street in years.

215
00:19:46,927 --> 00:19:50,139
我一直想起过去那些
美好的事情艾玛他样子怎麽了?
I keep remembering those things.
All the old things.

216
00:19:50,347 --> 00:19:53,559
<i>还是没变对吧?
Emmy, how's he look?
Same old Charles, eh?</i>

217
00:19:53,768 --> 00:19:56,479
罗杰安妮
去拿那些包
Roger, Ann, get these other bags.

218
00:20:00,816 --> 00:20:04,070
<i>你就住在查莉的房间里
You have Charlie's room
right here at the head of the stairs.</i>

219
00:20:04,278 --> 00:20:08,616
艾玛本想安妮搬出来的
但查理说你在这里会舒服些
Emmy wanted to move Ann, but Charlie
thought you'd be more comfortable here.

220
00:20:08,824 --> 00:20:10,785
<i>来吧罗杰
Come on, Roger.</i>

221
00:20:10,993 --> 00:20:14,288
-别把帽子放在床上啊
-你也迷信吗祖?
- Ah-ah! Don't put the hat on the bed.
- Superstitious, Joe?

222
00:20:14,497 --> 00:20:17,375
不但我不想
带来什麽麻烦事
No, but I don't believe in inviting trouble.

223
00:21:02,795 --> 00:21:05,548
那游艇并不是最大的
但在图书馆里有壁炉...
It wasn't the biggest yacht in the world,
but it had a fireplace in the library

224
00:21:05,756 --> 00:21:08,634
酒吧的面板都是桃木做的
and the bar was panelled
in bleached mahogany.

225
00:21:08,843 --> 00:21:13,347
只要按那个键...好了
不说我的
You pushed a button and...
What am I talking about? That's all over.

226
00:21:13,556 --> 00:21:15,307
<i>说说你们吧
Let's talk about you.</i>

227
00:21:15,516 --> 00:21:18,936
查莉这是我见你
穿过的最漂亮的裙子啊
Charlie,
that's the prettiest dress I ever saw.

228
00:21:19,145 --> 00:21:20,980
<i>我也这样认为啊
I think so, too.</i>

229
00:21:21,188 --> 00:21:23,607
查理你忘记了吗?
Why, Charles, don't you remember?

230
00:21:23,816 --> 00:21:25,609
忘记?忘记什麽?
Remember? Remember what?

231
00:21:25,818 --> 00:21:28,320
查理叔叔
这是你寄给我的是吗?
- Why, Uncle Charlie, you sent it to me.
- I did?

232
00:21:28,529 --> 00:21:31,490
是啊看我
总是忘了一些事情
Well, say, I've been sitting here
all this time forgetting something.

233
00:21:31,699 --> 00:21:34,535
安妮罗杰
Ann. Roger.

234
00:21:34,744 --> 00:21:38,789
-看看你们
-祖不知道你有没有
- Look at that. Oh, dear now.
- Joe. Don't know whether you had one.

235
00:21:38,998 --> 00:21:42,793
不用给我买礼物吧
给孩子们就可以了
You didn't have to think of me, Charles.
Presents for the children are alright.

236
00:21:43,002 --> 00:21:45,755
噢...我还没有过
一苹腕表呢
Say... I've never had a wristwatch.

237
00:21:45,963 --> 00:21:48,716
银行里的同事
还说我是运动型呢
Fellows at the bank'll think
I'm quite a sport.

238
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,179
<i>艾玛你有两份
一新一旧
I have two for you, Emmy.
One old and one new.</i>

239
00:21:53,387 --> 00:21:55,723
<i>噢查理
是什麽呢?
Oh, Charles. What is it?</i>

240
00:21:55,931 --> 00:21:59,060
<i>你真是...
- You shouldn't have. Really. No.
- Well, yeah.</i>

241
00:22:00,811 --> 00:22:03,856
噢查理
Oh, Charles.

242
00:22:04,065 --> 00:22:07,318
多麽漂亮啊
Oh, how... beautiful.

243
00:22:07,526 --> 00:22:09,403
我总想有一件的
Oh, I've-I've always wanted one.

244
00:22:09,612 --> 00:22:12,573
是啊妈妈
你应该有一件的
Oh, Mother, it's exactly right.
It's what you should have.

245
00:22:12,782 --> 00:22:14,825
看看
Look, Emmy.

246
00:22:19,872 --> 00:22:23,042
查理你一直带在身边
Charles. You've had these all along.

247
00:22:23,250 --> 00:22:26,212
<i>是啊艾玛很多年了
Mm-hm. All along, Emmy.
All these years.</i>

248
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:28,964
无论去哪里
都存放在保险箱
Safe in a deposit box,
no matter where I was.

249
00:22:29,173 --> 00:22:31,175
噢是外公和外婆吗?
Oh. Grandpa and Grandma?

250
00:22:31,384 --> 00:22:33,552
1888年
1888.

251
00:22:33,761 --> 00:22:35,805
<i>53年前了
53 years ago.</i>

252
00:22:36,013 --> 00:22:38,474
-他们很和蔼对吗?
-噢她很美啊
Aren't they sweet?
My, she was pretty.

253
00:22:38,682 --> 00:22:42,103
在那个时候
每个人都很美的
Everybody was sweet and pretty then.
The whole world.

254
00:22:42,311 --> 00:22:45,856
一个精彩的世界
不像现在的那样
A wonderful world.
Not like the world today.

255
00:22:47,066 --> 00:22:49,235
不像现在的世界
Not like the world now.

256
00:22:49,443 --> 00:22:51,237
那时候年轻真好
It was great to be young then.

257
00:22:51,445 --> 00:22:54,490
我们现在很开心啊
看看大家
We're all happy now, Uncle Charlie.
Look at us.

258
00:22:54,699 --> 00:22:58,619
-我们第一次同时那麽开心
-现在是你的礼物了查莉
- And we're all happy at the same time.
- Now, for your present, Charlie.

259
00:22:58,828 --> 00:23:03,207
噢我什麽都不需要
现在已经很满足了
Oh, I don't want anything.
Right now, I have enough.

260
00:23:03,416 --> 00:23:05,251
你来之前
我以为我需要很多东西
Before you came,
I didn't think I had anything,

261
00:23:05,459 --> 00:23:09,422
但现在我觉得不需要了
but now I don't want another thing.

262
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:12,341
-她傻了
-她并不是傻了
- She's crazy.
- She doesn't mean it.

263
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:15,928
她其实是在假装
像小说里面的女孩那样
If you ask me, I think she's putting on,
like girls in books.

264
00:23:16,137 --> 00:23:19,098
口里说不需要
而後来就什麽都想要
The ones that say they don't want
anything always get more in the end.

265
00:23:19,306 --> 00:23:22,351
-她是这样想的
-她不傻啊
- That's what she's hoping.
- She's not crazy.

266
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:24,437
在班里她是最聪明的
The smartest girl
in her class at school.

267
00:23:24,645 --> 00:23:29,442
<i>-独自一人在辩论赛中赢了里奇门中学辩论队
-她很有头脑的
Won the debate against theEast
Richmond HighSchool. She's got brains.</i>

268
00:23:34,155 --> 00:23:37,324
我是认真的
不必给我任何东西
I meant it.
Please don't give me anything.

269
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:39,994
-为什麽?
-我不知道怎麽解释
- Nothing?
- Oh, I can't explain it.

270
00:23:40,202 --> 00:23:45,124
你来了之後
妈妈很开心...
But you came here
and Mother's so happy and...

271
00:23:45,332 --> 00:23:49,503
噢我很高兴我们名字一样
Oh, I'm glad that she named me after you
and that she thinks we're both alike.

272
00:23:49,712 --> 00:23:53,299
我想我们是相同的
I think we are, too. I know it.

273
00:23:53,507 --> 00:23:56,927
你送我东西的话
会破坏事情的
Oh, it would spoil things
if you should give me anything.

274
00:23:57,136 --> 00:24:01,140
你真是个奇怪的女孩
那会破坏什麽事呢?
You're a strange girl, Charlie.
Why would it spoil things?

275
00:24:01,348 --> 00:24:06,145
因为我们并不仅
是叔叔和外甥女关系
Because we're not just an uncle
and a niece. It's something else.

276
00:24:06,353 --> 00:24:10,775
我了解你
别人了解你不多
I know you. I know that you don't
tell people a lot of things.

277
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:16,697
我觉得在你身上有些事情...
I don't either. I have a feeling
that inside you somewhere,

278
00:24:16,906 --> 00:24:19,950
<i>没有其他任何人知道
there's something nobody knows about.</i>

279
00:24:20,159 --> 00:24:22,453
没有人知道?
Something... nobody knows?

280
00:24:22,661 --> 00:24:26,207
是一些很惊奇的事情
我会知道的
Something secret and wonderful and...
I'll find it out.

281
00:24:26,415 --> 00:24:30,169
知道太多并不好啊查莉
It's not good
to find out too much, Charlie.

282
00:24:30,378 --> 00:24:33,047
我们就像双胞胎
不是吗?
But we're sort of like twins.
Don't you see?

283
00:24:33,255 --> 00:24:37,510
-我们都知道的
-把手给我查莉
- We have to know.
- Give me your hand, Charlie.

284
00:24:49,438 --> 00:24:51,857
谢谢你
Thank you.

285
00:24:52,066 --> 00:24:55,778
-你不看一眼啊
-我不需要看了
- You didn't even look at it.
- I don't have to.

286
00:24:55,986 --> 00:24:57,947
你送我什麽都是一样的
No matter what you gave me,
it'd be the same.

287
00:24:58,155 --> 00:25:00,032
让我给你看看吧
Here. Let me show you.

288
00:25:02,368 --> 00:25:06,038
这是一颗绿宝石
很漂亮的
It's a good emerald. A really good one.

289
00:25:09,083 --> 00:25:13,129
绿宝石是世上
最美丽的东西
Good emeralds are
the most beautiful things in the world.

290
00:25:20,010 --> 00:25:23,264
-你刻了一些字在上面
-没有啊如果你要我帮你拿去刻
- You've had something engraved.
- I haven't, but I will if you like it.

291
00:25:23,472 --> 00:25:25,891
有的查理叔叔
不过有点模糊
Yes, you have, Uncle Charlie.
It's very faint.

292
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:29,729
B.M赠予T.S
"T.S. From B.M."

293
00:25:29,937 --> 00:25:33,190
像是人名的缩写啊
