我想她要警惕一点
I thought she'd have better sense.

579
00:44:03,342 --> 00:44:04,927
<i>-你好
-你好
- How do you do?
- How do you do?</i>

580
00:44:05,136 --> 00:44:08,055
-你们应该就是来做调查的吧
-我是格翰牛顿太太
- You must have come to interview us.
- My name is Graham, Miss Newton.

581
00:44:08,264 --> 00:44:10,349
-你好
-这位是桑德斯
- Oh, how do you do?
- And this is Fred Saunders.

582
00:44:10,558 --> 00:44:12,685
你好   请进来
How do you do? Won't you come in?

583
00:44:12,893 --> 00:44:15,187
-我去叫妈妈
-谢谢
- I'll call my mother.
- Thank you.

584
00:44:15,396 --> 00:44:18,357
<i>妈妈他们进来了
Mother, the government men are here.</i>

585
00:44:18,566 --> 00:44:20,359
<i>请做
Will you sit down?</i>

586
00:44:20,568 --> 00:44:22,737
你们说是四点的
现在还没准备好啊
But you said 4:00. Nothing's ready now.

587
00:44:22,945 --> 00:44:25,072
我丈夫还在银行
而这里...
My husband is still at the bank
and-and the house is -

588
00:44:25,281 --> 00:44:27,658
我们就是想这样
牛顿太太
That's all we want now, Mrs Newton,
some pictures of the house.

589
00:44:27,867 --> 00:44:30,703
桑德斯会在周围拍照
而我就问你问题
Saunders can get busy
and I'd like to ask a few questions.

590
00:44:30,911 --> 00:44:35,458
好的但我希望你们
等我把房子收拾好了
Alright, but I do wish you'd waited
until I had the house looking its best.

591
00:44:35,666 --> 00:44:38,669
<i>我想在这里安放鲜花
还有在厨房里挂新的窗窗布
I wanted flowers around
and fresh curtains in the kitchen.</i>

592
00:44:38,878 --> 00:44:41,630
<i>还有很多东西我想你们拍照的
And there are a lot of things
I don't want you to photograph.</i>

593
00:44:42,465 --> 00:44:46,093
<i>-你们拥有这房子吗?
-不是房子拥有我们
- You said you own the house?
- Own it? It owns us.</i>

594
00:44:46,302 --> 00:44:49,889
有一样东西开始要修理的话
整间房子都要修理了
No sooner do I get one thing fixed
than something else gets broken.

595
00:44:50,097 --> 00:44:52,224
要再刷一下油漆...
And then it needs fresh paint and th-

596
00:44:52,433 --> 00:44:54,226
<i>桑德斯先生
不好意思...
Mr Saunders, I'm very sorry</i>

597
00:44:54,435 --> 00:44:56,479
<i>请不要给这张椅子拍照
but you simply cannot
take a picture with that chair in it.</i>

598
00:44:56,687 --> 00:45:00,274
<i>-要套一个沙发套
-你们家有六个人?
- It needs a new slipcover.
- And there are, uh, six in your family?</i>

599
00:45:00,483 --> 00:45:02,902
-是五个
-五个?但是...
- Five.
- Five? But -

600
00:45:03,110 --> 00:45:04,945
<i>我叔叔只是来探望我们的
Well, my uncle ' s just visiting.</i>

601
00:45:05,154 --> 00:45:06,989
<i>我说过他的
他是从东部来的
I told you about him.
He's here from the East.</i>

602
00:45:07,198 --> 00:45:10,326
我叔叔不希望有什麽麻烦
My uncle doesn't want to be bothered
with a lot of questions.

603
00:45:10,534 --> 00:45:12,661
做调查的时候我们要...
Well, you see, on a survey, we usually -

604
00:45:12,870 --> 00:45:14,663
<i>他对调查不感兴趣...
He's not interested
in a survey</i>

605
00:45:14,872 --> 00:45:17,124
<i>我答应过他不会骚扰他的
and I promised him
he wouldn ' t be bothered.</i>

606
00:45:17,333 --> 00:45:19,126
我们希望你们都参与
Well, we'd like it
if we could get all of you.

607
00:45:19,335 --> 00:45:21,504
想了解你们做什麽
和想做些什麽
You know, your opinions,
what you do or what you want to do.

608
00:45:21,712 --> 00:45:24,882
我叔叔的意见很特别的
我想你们不会接受
My uncle's opinions aren't average
and I'm afraid they wouldn't help you.

609
00:45:25,091 --> 00:45:28,427
<i>我想每个人都有自己的思想
I think when someone asks for privacy,
they should have it.</i>

610
00:45:28,636 --> 00:45:31,597
其实我们这次的目的是...
Well, we'll...
The whole idea of this thing is that -

611
00:45:31,806 --> 00:45:34,475
格翰先生我想你们应该
选择另外的家庭
Mr Graham, perhaps
you'd better choose another family.

612
00:45:35,393 --> 00:45:38,854
我们也有这样做的
但你们的家庭是...
We'll do anything you say, of course,
but this family seemed right and -

613
00:45:39,063 --> 00:45:40,856
<i>是一个很好的家庭
It is a nice family.</i>

614
00:45:41,065 --> 00:45:43,901
查莉你为什麽
不让他问下去呢?
Charlie, let the young men go ahead,
so long as they're here.

615
00:45:44,110 --> 00:45:46,362
那好吧
Well, alright.

616
00:45:46,570 --> 00:45:49,365
好的桑德斯
去拍些照片吧
OK. Saunders, go ahead
and get another shot.

617
00:45:49,573 --> 00:45:53,577
牛顿太太可以告诉
我你丈夫在哪里工作吗?
Mrs Newton, what organisations
do you and your husband belong to?

618
00:45:53,786 --> 00:45:55,579
在厨房照一张好吗?
How about a picture in the kitchen?

619
00:45:55,788 --> 00:45:58,958
我想不是很适合
Well, I'm afraid the kitchen
isn't quite the way I'd like it.

620
00:45:59,166 --> 00:46:01,210
<i>过来
Come along.</i>

621
00:46:06,716 --> 00:46:08,968
牛顿太太
你要先打鸡蛋吧
If you'll start by breakin' an egg,
Mrs Newton.

622
00:46:09,176 --> 00:46:10,886
噢不不应该先打蛋的
Oh, but you don't start a cake
by breaking an egg.

623
00:46:11,095 --> 00:46:13,180
要先把牛油和糖放进去
You have to put
the butter and sugar in first.

624
00:46:13,389 --> 00:46:17,309
有没有调查
我都不会先打蛋的
Survey or no survey,
I'm not going to start by breaking an egg.

625
00:46:17,518 --> 00:46:21,188
<i>我要做一个枫叶蛋糕
我弟弟很爱吃的
I thought I'd make a maple cake.
My brother Charles loves maple cake.</i>

626
00:46:21,397 --> 00:46:24,567
-你弟弟做什麽的?
-我想他什麽都做
What does your brother do?
I guess he just does about everything.

627
00:46:24,775 --> 00:46:28,571
-是什麽工作?
-应该是做生意的男人都是那样
What does he do? He's just in business.
You know, the way men are.

628
00:46:28,779 --> 00:46:33,325
我丈夫在银行
但我想查理是生意人
My husband works in a bank,
but I think Charles is just in business.

629
00:46:33,534 --> 00:46:36,829
<i>如果你要在
我打蛋的时候拍照
If you really want a picture
of me breaking an egg,</i>

630
00:46:37,038 --> 00:46:39,832
那就要等我把
牛油和糖放进去
you'll have to wait
till I cream the butter and sugar.

631
00:46:40,041 --> 00:46:41,834
我会等的
I'll wait.

632
00:46:42,043 --> 00:46:44,003
我可以到楼上看看吗?
I wonder if we could
take a look upstairs.

633
00:46:44,211 --> 00:46:46,005
请你带我去吧
你妈妈会叫我的好的
You show us, and your mother can call us
when she's ready.

634
00:46:46,213 --> 00:46:49,133
桑德斯先生
- Alright.
- If you'd rather wait, Mr Saunders.

635
00:46:49,341 --> 00:46:52,011
加蛋的时间要很及时
Folding in the eggs
has to be done just right.

636
00:46:52,219 --> 00:46:54,013
<i>不能让它等得太久
I can ' t beat them and let them stand.</i>

637
00:46:54,221 --> 00:46:56,515
我一听到你打蛋的声音
就马上下来
The minute I hear you've
broken the eggs, I'll come right down.

638
00:46:56,724 --> 00:46:57,725
好的
Yes.

639
00:47:04,565 --> 00:47:07,234
我不知道你想找什麽
I really don't see
what you want to look up here for.

640
00:47:07,443 --> 00:47:10,738
那间房是谁的?本来
是我的现在查理叔叔住著
Whose room is that? It's mine.
My uncle's using it now, though.

641
00:47:10,946 --> 00:47:14,617
我想知道
里面的布局是怎样的
I'd like to see what your room looks like.
Typical girl, typical room.

642
00:47:14,825 --> 00:47:17,328
但我叔叔正在休息
Typical of you to ask.
My uncle's resting.

643
00:47:17,536 --> 00:47:19,622
我不想打扰他
I really don't want to disturb him.

644
00:47:19,830 --> 00:47:24,168
-那是後楼梯吗?
-没错可以到大厅的
- Is there a back stairs?
- Mm-hm. Right down the hall.

645
00:47:24,377 --> 00:47:26,921
我和你打赌
你叔叔不在里面
I'll bet you 50 cents
that your uncle isn't in there.

646
00:47:27,129 --> 00:47:28,923
打赌很无聊的
Oh, betting's silly.

647
00:47:29,131 --> 00:47:31,884
你只是想进去拍照
All you want to do
is photograph my room, doesn't he?

648
00:47:32,093 --> 00:47:34,970
我知道叔叔在里面
- That's it.
- Besides, I know my uncle's in there.

649
00:47:35,179 --> 00:47:37,682
但我还是认为他在里面
我们进去看看吧
Alright, I'll still bet he isn't.
Let me knock and see.

650
00:47:37,890 --> 00:47:40,393
我先敲门
Oh, I'll knock.

651
00:47:40,601 --> 00:47:43,187
查理叔叔?
Uncle Charlie?

652
00:47:43,396 --> 00:47:45,690
查理叔叔
我们可以进来吗?
Uncle Charlie, may we come in?

653
00:47:51,404 --> 00:47:53,948
-看到了吗?
-你说得对
- See?
- You were right.

654
00:47:54,156 --> 00:47:56,867
不错的房间啊
可以拍几张照片吗?
Nice room. Do you mind if I take a picture
since he isn't here?

655
00:47:57,076 --> 00:47:59,912
-我真的不想打扰你叔叔
-我知道
- I don't want to disturb your uncle.
- Oh, I suppose so.

656
00:48:00,121 --> 00:48:03,708
但我想不到
谁会对我的房间感兴趣
But I really can't imagine
anyone being interested in my room.

657
00:48:03,916 --> 00:48:08,671
我喜欢现在的颜色
我喜欢全部是白色
It's not the way I'd like it.
I'd like to have it yellow and white.

658
00:48:08,879 --> 00:48:10,673
他想享受宁静啊
Might as well let him work in peace.

659
00:48:10,881 --> 00:48:14,468
我想和他说几句
Besides, I'd like to talk to you.

660
00:48:14,677 --> 00:48:18,514
你说我们是普通家庭
但我觉得很有意思
Your picking us as an average family
gave me a funny feeling.

661
00:48:18,723 --> 00:48:22,560
-什麽有意思?
-我不知道
- What kind of a funny feeling?
- Oh, I don't know.

662
00:48:22,768 --> 00:48:25,479
我想是我不想
做一个普通女孩吧
I guess I don't like to be and average girl
in an average family.

663
00:48:25,688 --> 00:48:27,606
普通家庭才是好的
看看我
Average families are the best.
Look at me.

664
00:48:27,815 --> 00:48:30,109
<i>-我也是来自普通家庭的
-和我们一样普通?
- I'm from an average family.
- As average as ours?</i>

665
00:48:30,317 --> 00:48:32,486
当然是了
但我还不确定你们很普通
Sure.
Besides, I don't think you're average.

666
00:48:32,695 --> 00:48:36,991
那是因为你们现在来这里
而不是前几天
Oh, that's because you see me now
instead of a few days ago.

667
00:48:37,199 --> 00:48:42,455
我那时很灰暗
查理叔叔来了就改变了
I was in the dumps. Then Uncle Charlie
came and everything changed.

668
00:48:42,663 --> 00:48:45,541
但你妈妈说他昨晚才到的
可能你...
But your mother said he came last night.
Maybe you just think -

669
00:48:45,750 --> 00:48:48,461
我知道的
I don't think. I know.

670
00:48:48,669 --> 00:48:53,841
很有趣每次我想东西的时候
总会想到查理叔叔
Funny, but when I think about how I feel,
I always come back to Uncle Charlie.

671
00:48:54,050 --> 00:48:58,054
而你不想让我
觉得他很不简单吗?
Are you trying to tell me
I shouldn't think he's so wonderful?

672
00:48:59,847 --> 00:49:02,808
<i>-噢我只是...
-桑德斯先生?
- Oh, no. I -
- Mr Saunders?</i>

673
00:49:03,017 --> 00:49:06,645
<i>我准备好打蛋了希望
桑德斯先生不会搞得很乱
- I'm ready with the eggs.
- Mr Saunders mustn't move anything.</i>

674
00:49:06,854 --> 00:49:10,483
<i>-我叔叔是很整洁和挑剔的
-桑德斯先生也是的
- My uncle's awfully neat and fussy.
- Saunders is neat and fussy, too.</i>

675
00:49:15,529 --> 00:49:18,783
<i>-这是你提起的叔叔吗?
-是的
- Is this your uncle?
- Yes, it is.</i>

676
00:49:23,079 --> 00:49:25,456
现在来一张走廊的
Now, for one of the hall.

677
00:49:27,625 --> 00:49:29,877
<i>桑德斯先生在
我房间拍了几张照片
Mr Saunders has been
taking pictures of my room.</i>

678
00:49:30,086 --> 00:49:34,256
我姐姐提醒你们
那些鸡蛋和蛋糕
My sister told me to remind you
about eggs and a cake.

679
00:49:34,465 --> 00:49:37,510
我不想被拍照
我要拿回那底片
I don't like to be photographed.
I'll have to ask you for the film.

680
00:49:37,718 --> 00:49:40,846
-噢查理叔叔
-请给我
- Oh, Uncle Charlie.
- Give it to me, please.

681
00:49:41,055 --> 00:49:43,516
给他吧桑德斯
Give it to him, Fred.

682
00:49:43,724 --> 00:49:47,937
真可惜牛顿太太
的照片也在里面
That's too bad. There's a picture
of Mrs Newton on this film.

683
00:49:54,735 --> 00:49:58,698
<i>不好意思桑德斯先生
我准备好加蛋了
- Excuse me.
- The eggs are ready.</i>

684
00:49:58,906 --> 00:50:01,617
<i>我不能再让它等著了
I can't let them stand another minute.</i>

685
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:07,206
-那是最後一卷胶卷了
-噢
That was my last roll of film.

686
00:50:07,415 --> 00:50:09,709
桑德斯先生
给查理叔叔拍照...
Mr Saunders took
Uncle Charlie's picture by mistake

687
00:50:09,917 --> 00:50:12,586
查理叔叔把胶卷拿了
and Uncle Charlie made him
give him back the roll.

688
00:50:12,753 --> 00:50:15,423
他不是在开玩笑的
He wasn't joking
about not wanting to be photographed.

689
00:50:15,589 --> 00:50:17,383
我们都不想
有什麽家庭纠纷
We didn't want to start a family feud.

690
00:50:17,591 --> 00:50:19,385
我们明天再来
看你做蛋糕吧
I'll get you
making the cake again tomorrow.

691
00:50:19,593 --> 00:50:21,929
我明天不会做蛋糕了
I won't be
making a cake again tomorrow.

692
00:50:22,138 --> 00:50:25,599
我要做一些
很重要的事情
I want to help an important work,
but I cannot go on making cakes.

693
00:50:25,808 --> 00:50:28,644
你已经帮我们了
牛顿太太
You have helped, Mrs Newton.

694
00:50:28,853 --> 00:50:30,646
我还想问一下
And now I'd like to ask another favour.

695
00:50:30,855 --> 00:50:34,066
今天晚上可以约你的女儿
出去吗?我想四处看看
Could I borrow your daughter?
I'd like to look around the town.

696
00:50:34,275 --> 00:50:37,069
-安妮?
-是查莉
- Ann?
- Charlie.

697
00:50:37,278 --> 00:50:41,240
安妮会好些
她什麽都知道
Ann would be better.
Ann knows everything about everybody.

698
00:50:41,449 --> 00:50:45,202
-查莉
-如果查莉不介意的话
- Charlie.
- Well, if, uh, Charlie doesn't mind.

699
00:50:45,411 --> 00:50:47,913
-我不介意
-太好了
- I don't mind.
- Swell.

700
00:50:54,754 --> 00:50:56,047
-再见牛顿太太
-再见
- Goodbye, then, Mrs Newton.
- Goodbye.

701
00:50:56,255 --> 00:50:58,549
-六点半好吗?
-六点半
- 6:30?
- 6:30.

702
00:50:58,758 --> 00:50:59,759
-好的再见
-再见
- OK. Goodbye.
- Bye.

703
00:50:59,967 --> 00:51:01,635
-再见桑德斯先生
再见
- Bye, Mr Saunders.
- Bye.

704
00:51:01,844 --> 00:51:03,512
再见
Goodbye.

705
00:51:04,847 --> 00:51:07,183
看来他是一个
不错的年轻人啊
He seems like a nice young man.

706
00:51:07,391 --> 00:51:10,144
你不是要和
卡芙琳去看电影吗?
But I thought you were
going to the movies with Catherine.

707
00:51:10,353 --> 00:51:13,189
我会告诉她我有点不舒服
Oh, I'll tell her
I don't feel well or something.

708
00:51:29,080 --> 00:51:32,291
-你好啊查莉
-你们好啊卡芙琳雪莉
- Hello, Charlie.
- Well... hello, Catherine. Hello, Shirley.

709
00:51:32,500 --> 00:51:36,754
-你们好
-这位是格翰他刚来这里
- Hello.
- This is Jack Graham. He's in town.

710
00:51:36,962 --> 00:51:38,756
-你好
-你好
- How do you do?
- Hello.

711
00:51:38,964 --> 00:51:43,386
-你的喉咙好点了吗查莉?
-好很多了谢谢
- How's your throat, Charlie?
- Oh, much better. Thank you.

712
00:51:43,594 --> 00:51:45,638
比尔在问你的事呢
Bill Forest was asking about you.

713
00:51:45,846 --> 00:51:48,265
噢比尔?
Oh. Bill Forest?

714
00:51:48,474 --> 00:51:50,559
再见了
Well, uh... goodbye.

715
00:51:50,768 --> 00:51:52,812
-再见
-再见
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

716
00:52:01,362 --> 00:52:03,406
我知道你其实是什麽人
I know what you are, really.

717
00:52:03,614 --> 00:52:07,118
你是侦探
You're a detective. There's something
the matter and you're a detective.

718
00:52:07,326 --> 00:52:09,745
-有些事情是侦探会做的
-听我说查莉
- Charlie, listen.
- I don't want to listen.

719
00:52:09,954 --> 00:52:11,414
我不想听你们根本
就不是来做调查
Why, you're not on a survey at all.

720
00:52:11,622 --> 00:52:13,416
你对我们说谎
你们骗了我妈妈
You lied to us. You lied to Mother.

721
00:52:13,624 --> 00:52:16,752
你们只是想进我们家里
You just wanted to get in our house.
Police.

722
00:52:16,961 --> 00:52:18,713
就是那样
That's what it is.

723
00:52:18,921 --> 00:52:22,091
你们为什麽要骗我们?
What do you want with us?
Why are you here, lying to us?

724
00:52:22,299 --> 00:52:24,260
查莉你要听我说
你一定要相信我
Look, Charlie, you've got to listen to me.
You've got to trust me.

725
00:52:24,468 --> 00:52:26,262
你说谎也要相信你吗?
When you've done nothing but lie?

726
00:52:26,470 --> 00:52:29,140
我知道你并不是
想和我约会
And you probably didn't want to
take me out at all the way I thought.

727
00:52:29,348 --> 00:52:31,308
你只是想问我很多问题
You just wanted to ask me
a lot of questions.

728
00:52:31,517 --> 00:52:34,311
我有那样做吗有吗?
Have I asked you a lot of questions?
Have I?

729
00:52:34,520 --> 00:52:37,857
好了我的确是侦探
还做得很糟糕
Alright, I'm a detective.
A pretty bad one.

730
00:52:38,065 --> 00:52:39,859
你听我说几句好吗?
Now, won't you even listen to me?

731
00:52:40,067 --> 00:52:42,319
-为什麽你要骗我?
-我必须那样做
- Why should I when you lied to me?
- I had to.

732
00:52:42,528 --> 00:52:45,197
我来这里的目的
是为了一个男人不是你
When I came here to find a man,
I hadn't counted on you.

733
00:52:45,364 --> 00:52:49,160
-不是你妈妈和你家人
-一个男人?什麽男人?
- I hadn't counted on your family.
- Find a man? What man?

734
00:52:49,368 --> 00:52:51,829
我们在追踪一个在逃的人
There's a man loose in this country.
We're after him.

735
00:52:52,038 --> 00:52:55,332
我们知道的很少
连他的样子都不知道
We don't know much.
We don't even know what he looks like.

736
00:52:55,541 --> 00:52:59,503
查莉你对你叔叔了解有多少?
Charlie, think. How much
do you know about your uncle?

737
00:52:59,712 --> 00:53:03,799
他是我妈妈的弟弟
他有什麽问题?
Why, he's my mother's brother.
What's he got to do with it?

738
00:53:04,008 --> 00:53:05,968
我们要找的人
可能是你叔叔
This man we want may be your uncle.

739
00:53:06,177 --> 00:53:09,805
噢我不相信
别再烦著我
Oh, I don't believe you.
Go away and leave me alone.

740
00:53:10,014 --> 00:53:13,434
我们追踪的那个男人
很可能就是你叔叔
We're after one man.
Your uncle may be that man.

741
00:53:13,642 --> 00:53:17,021
但在东部还有
另一个男人在被追捕
But in the East, there's another man
who's being hunted too,

742
00:53:17,229 --> 00:53:19,607
从麻省到缅因
他可能就是那个人
through Massachusetts and into Maine.
He may be the one.

743
00:53:19,815 --> 00:53:22,026
我叔叔没做什麽
My uncle hasn't done anything.

744
00:53:22,234 --> 00:53:24,945
他知道那会对我妈妈不好
He knows it would kill
my mother if he did.

745
00:53:25,154 --> 00:53:28,824
他是我妈妈的弟弟
就像罗杰和我一样
He's her younger brother,
just like Roger is mine.

746
00:53:29,033 --> 00:53:30,910
他们为什麽不把
在东部那人捉了?
Why don't they arrest
that man in the East?

747
00:53:31,118 --> 00:53:34,330
<i>你们为什麽还要烦我们?
Why don't you go away
and leave us alone?</i>

748
00:53:34,538 --> 00:53:37,500
查莉我们晚餐时
谈起各自的亲人...
Charlie, when we were eating tonight
and talking about our folks

749
00:53:37,708 --> 00:53:41,128
就像平常人一样
and what we'd done and how we felt,
we were like two ordinary people.

750
00:53:41,337 --> 00:53:43,255
我们都在同样环境中成长
We'd been brought up about the same.

751
00:53:43,464 --> 00:53:47,343
<i>-我们彼此都有好感
-噢现在已不重要了
- You liked me and I liked you.
- Oh, it doesn't matter now.</i>

752
00:53:47,551 --> 00:53:50,680
什麽不重要这点才重要
What do you mean, "It doesn't matter"?
It's the only thing that does.

753
00:53:50,888 --> 00:53:53,099
<i>如果不是你的叔叔...
If it weren't for you,
you don't think I ' d care</i>

754
00:53:53,307 --> 00:53:55,226
<i>我早\'就把他逮捕了
知道吗?
how or where I caught up
with your uncle, do you?</i>

755
00:53:55,434 --> 00:53:59,647
因为如果他真的是我们要的人
我们就要捉住他
Because if he's the guy, I'm going to
catch up with him. Remember that.

756
00:53:59,855 --> 00:54:02,024
<i>你必须保守秘密
And you're going to keep
your mouth shut.</i>

757
00:54:02,233 --> 00:54:04,902
<i>因为你是个很好的女孩
如果你知道了...
You're going to keep your mouth shut
because you're such a nice girl</i>

758
00:54:05,069 --> 00:54:08,781
你就会帮你叔叔
you'd help if you knew
your uncle was the man we wanted.

759
00:54:08,989 --> 00:54:11,742
<i>-我不会帮你们的
-我知道你会的
- I wouldn't help you.
- And I know you would.</i>

760
00:54:11,951 --> 00:54:14,245
让我再给你一个好些的条件
And I'm trying to make it easier for you.

761
00:54:14,453 --> 00:54:17,456
如果你叔叔真的是那个人
我们会平静地把他从这里带走
If your uncle's the man we want,
we'll get him out of town quietly.

762
00:54:17,665 --> 00:54:20,418
<i>-我们不会在这里逮捕他
-在这?在妈妈面前逮捕他?
- We won't arrest him here.
- Arrest him here? With mother -</i>

763
00:54:20,626 --> 00:54:23,462
<i>我想对你说我们不会的
I'm trying to tell you we won ' t.</i>

764
00:54:25,297 --> 00:54:29,385
-求你了查莉
-我什麽也不会说的
- Please, Charlie.
- I won't say anything.

765
00:54:29,593 --> 00:54:31,971
噢送我回家吧!
Oh, take me home!

766
00:54:45,818 --> 00:54:47,653
晚安查莉
Good night, Charlie.

767
00:54:47,862 --> 00:54:50,865
你们发现做错了
就一定很有趣
It's going to be funny
when you find out you're wrong.

768
00:54:51,073 --> 00:54:53,409
晚安
Good night.

769
00:55:25,608 --> 00:55:27,568
<i>-你好啊查莉回来了吗?
-是的爸爸
- Hello, Charlie. Home already?
- Oh, yes, Dad.</i>

770
00:55:27,777 --> 00:55:30,821
外面空气很好
我想出去呼吸一下
It's so nice out, I thought
I'd get some air before I went to bed.

771
00:55:31,030 --> 00:55:34,325
你最好快点回来
查理叔叔找你
You better run in. Your Uncle Charlie's
been asking about you.

772
00:55:34,533 --> 00:55:36,494
我会在後门上去的
I think I'll just go up the back way.

773
00:55:36,702 --> 00:55:38,496
我很累不是很想说话
I- I'm tired and I don't feel like talking.

774
00:55:38,704 --> 00:55:41,082
好的换衣服吧
Alright. Suit yourself.

775
00:55:41,290 --> 00:55:43,042
小心照顾自己啊
- Take care of yourself.
- Mm-hm.

776
00:55:43,250 --> 00:55:45,086
-晚安贺博
-晚安查莉
- Good night, Herb.
- Good night, Charlie.

777
00:55:45,294 --> 00:55:46,879
晚安查莉
Good night, Charlie.

778
00:55:47,088 --> 00:55:49,924
我们在说什麽贺博?
What were we saying, Herb?
Did I notice what?

779
00:55:50,132 --> 00:55:51,884
觉得有点什麽不妥吗...
Well, did you taste anything funny

780
00:55:52,093 --> 00:55:54,178
你今晚在我家喝的咖啡?
about that coffee you had
at my house this evening?

781
00:55:54,387 --> 00:55:56,430
没有啊
No. It tasted all right.

782
00:55:56,639 --> 00:55:58,683
这就对了
那里面有点不同
That's what I mean. It wasn't all right.

783
00:55:58,891 --> 00:56:01,560
-放了什麽?
-一点苏打水
- Put something in it?
- Put a little soda.

784
00:56:01,769 --> 00:56:05,189
如果我放毒药的话
也是这份量
About the same amount that I'd have used
if I'd wanted to use poison.

785
00:56:05,398 --> 00:56:07,817
你不说我还不察觉呢
Well, you don't say?
I never tasted a thing.

786
00:56:08,025 --> 00:56:10,945
当然我连苏打
也察觉不到
Of course, I might not notice the soda.

787
00:56:11,153 --> 00:56:14,782
更别提无色无味的毒药
You'd notice the soda more
than you would the poison.

788
00:56:14,990 --> 00:56:17,076
如果是的话
你现在早\'死了
For all you knew, you might
just as well be dead now.

789
00:56:47,648 --> 00:56:50,359
-安妮还没睡吗?
-是啊
- Aren't you asleep yet, Ann?
- Uh-uh.

790
00:57:02,288 --> 00:57:04,498
查莉你在干嘛?
Charlotte, what are you doing?

791
00:57:04,707 --> 00:57:07,501
噢我在找我看过的新闻
Oh, I'm just looking for a recipe
I thought I saw,

792
00:57:07,710 --> 00:57:10,212
但这已经给撕破了--
but it's just so torn up.

793
00:57:10,421 --> 00:57:13,507
图书馆里什麽报纸都有
They have papers in the "libarry",
new ones and old ones.

794
00:57:13,716 --> 00:57:15,468
柯克然小姐会帮你找的
Miss Corcoran will get them out for you.

795
00:57:15,676 --> 00:57:19,180
就算你剪下来一点
她都不会发现的
She won't even notice
if you cut out a little, bitty recipe.

796
00:57:19,388 --> 00:57:21,640
那也不是什麽重要的东西
Oh, it's not that important.

797
00:57:22,892 --> 00:57:24,268
图书馆几时关门?
What time does the library close?

798
00:57:24,477 --> 00:57:29,607
如果你平时多去的话
就会知道是9点
If you read as much as you should,
you'd know it closes at 9:00.

799
00:57:30,691 --> 00:57:34,987
这样啊那我明天才去吧
Oh, well.
If I think about it, maybe I'll go tomorrow.

800
00:57:35,196 --> 00:57:37,698
你该睡了
You really ought to go to sleep, Ann.

801
00:58:22,952 --> 00:58:25,830
回去!回去!回去!
Get back there!
Get back! Get back!

802
00:58:36,841 --> 00:58:39,719
查莉等一下
知道我为什麽在这吗?
Just a moment, Charlie.
What do you think I am out here for?

803
00:58:39,927 --> 00:58:41,846
对不起诺顿警官
Oh, I'm sorry, Mr Norton.

804
00:58:42,054 --> 00:58:44,098
没事了走吧
Alright. Go ahead.

805
00:59:24,722 --> 00:59:27,391
噢柯克然小姐
请让我进去!
Oh! Miss Corcoran, please let me in.

806
00:59:27,558 --> 00:59:29,602
求求你!
Oh, please!

807
00:59:32,271 --> 00:59:33,981
太谢谢你了
Oh, thank you.

808
00:59:34,190 --> 00:59:37,109
查莉你真是的
明知道这里9点关门
Really, Charlie. You know as well as I do
the library closes at 9:00.

809
00:59:37,318 --> 00:59:39,236
如果我这次给你例外
以後还得了
If I make one exception,
I'll have to make a thousand.

810
00:59:39,445 --> 00:59:43,115
对不起柯克然小姐
我要找出那报纸
I'm sorry, Mrs Corcoran, but there is something
in the paper I've got to see.

811
00:59:43,324 --> 00:59:45,659
太令我惊讶了
你都不为别人著想
I'm surprised at you, Charlie.
No consideration.

812
00:59:45,868 --> 00:59:48,537
-我只需要一分钟
-你一大早\'又不来
- Oh, I'll only be a minute.
- You've got all day to come here.

813
00:59:48,746 --> 00:59:51,290
真不知道你为啥
夜晚赶来这里
I don't know why you want
to rush in here tonight like a madwoman.

814
00:59:51,499 --> 00:59:54,043
我只给你三分钟
I'll give you just three minutes.

815
01:00:10,393 --> 01:00:13,938
老天保佑不要是坏消息
Can't be anything really awful.

816
01:00:14,146 --> 01:00:16,816
我会证明他不是的
I'll prove to him it isn't.

817
01:00:18,192 --> 01:00:20,277
第三版--
Page three -

818
01:01:57,458 --> 01:01:59,085
你好
Hello.

819
01:01:59,293 --> 01:02:03,631
-查莉在哪?
-她还在睡我不想吵醒她
- Where's Charlie?
- Still asleep. I don't want to wake her.

820
01:02:13,766 --> 01:02:16,143
-查莉还在睡吗?
-不她刚醒来
- Charlie still asleep?
- No, she just woke up.

821
01:02:16,352 --> 01:02:20,064
我不该让她睡那麽久
但她好像很累
I shouldn't have let her sleep so long,
but she needed it.

822
01:02:20,272 --> 01:02:23,859
她有点不舒服
她会下来吃饭的
She doesn't look quite herself.
She'll be down for dinner.

823
01:02:45,381 --> 01:02:47,258
妈妈让我来捣碎这些
Mother, let me finish mashing those.

824
01:02:47,466 --> 01:02:50,344
我来弄晚餐吧
I'll fix the rest of dinner
and get it on the table.

825
01:02:50,553 --> 01:02:51,804
你去跟查理叔叔聊吧
You go talk to Uncle Charlie.

826
01:02:52,013 --> 01:02:53,764
-你觉得怎麽样?
-我没事
- How do you feel?
- Fine.

827
01:02:53,973 --> 01:02:56,392
我累极了
睡得死死的
I must have been tired. I slept like a log.

828
01:02:56,684 --> 01:02:59,854
查理叔叔找你很多次了
他很喜欢你
Uncle Charlie was asking for you again.
He's fond of you.

829
01:03:00,062 --> 01:03:05,651
那年轻人也来过两次
我说你睡了
That nice young man came to ask
after you. I told him you were asleep.

830
01:03:05,860 --> 01:03:10,781
<i>我又恢复精神了
这肉汁弄好了吗?
I'm rested now. Is the gravy made?</i>

831
01:03:12,033 --> 01:03:16,704
你又在哼那华尔兹曲了
Now you're humming that waltz.
Please don't hum that tune anymore.

832
01:03:16,912 --> 01:03:19,832
我好不容易才忘了它
I've just got it out of my head
and don't want it started again.

833
01:03:20,041 --> 01:03:22,543
不要再哼了
Please remember, don't hum that tune.

834
01:03:22,752 --> 01:03:25,004
不要每次都站起来
And don't keep getting up
every few minutes.

835
01:03:25,212 --> 01:03:26,756
只要像个淑女那样
静静坐著
You just sit there and be a real lady.

836
01:03:26,964 --> 01:03:31,218
那好吧
至少我能把汤端出去
Alright, if you say so,
but at least I can carry in the soup.

837
01:03:31,427 --> 01:03:37,099
罗杰快洗手!
祖查理吃饭了
Roger, wash your hands!
Joe. Charles. Dinner.

838
01:03:38,726 --> 01:03:43,647
妈妈安妮我说过
不要把东西挂在耳後
- Mama -
- Ann, don't put things behind your ear.

839
01:03:43,856 --> 01:03:46,942
别低声说谁都知道
你在说坏话
And don't whisper.
Anyone could hear you a block away.

840
01:03:47,151 --> 01:03:48,694
我能跟你坐吗?
May I sit by you at the table?

841
01:03:48,903 --> 01:03:51,906
<i>跟我?我还以为
你想跟查理叔叔坐呢
By me? I should think
you'd want to sit by Uncle Charlie.</i>

842
01:03:52,114 --> 01:03:55,326
<i>-不我想跟你坐
-为什麽想换?
- No, I want to sit by you.
- Why do you want to change?</i>

843
01:03:55,534 --> 01:03:57,328
妈妈就让她换吧
Mother, let her change if she wants to.

844
01:03:57,536 --> 01:03:59,580
罗杰说不介意
Roger doesn't mind.

845
01:03:59,789 --> 01:04:03,751
他当然不介意
但查理叔叔会不能
No, certainly not.
Uncle Charlie might think... Certainly not.

846
01:04:03,959 --> 01:04:08,547
-妈妈让她换吧
-好吧安妮总是有怪念头
- Mother, let her change.
- OK, but Ann has some foolish ideas.

847
01:04:08,756 --> 01:04:12,385
你们都去饭厅吧
Go in the dining room, both of you.

848
01:04:19,725 --> 01:04:22,687
什麽事了?
安妮不跟我坐了吗?
What's going on here?
Have I lost my little girl?

849
01:04:22,895 --> 01:04:25,231
<i>罗杰想跟你坐
Roger wanted to sit next to you,</i>

850
01:04:25,439 --> 01:04:28,442
我想让孩子们换换座位
and I thought it would be nice
if the children took turns.

851
01:04:28,651 --> 01:04:30,277
-我才不想--
-不想什麽罗杰?
- I never...
- Never what, Roger?

852
01:04:30,486 --> 01:04:34,782
没事安妮快来帮我
- Nothing.
- Come, Ann. Come and help me.

853
01:04:34,990 --> 01:04:40,079
祖!   我不该把报纸
带到饭桌上没特别的新闻
Joe! I brought it in by mistake.
Nothing special in it.

854
01:04:40,287 --> 01:04:43,582
-查理想看一下吗?
-谢谢祖
- Want to look at the headlines, Charles?
- Thank you, Joe.

855
01:04:45,626 --> 01:04:48,337
<i>罗杰喝汤不要发出声音
Roger, don't make so much noise
with your soup.</i>

856
01:04:48,546 --> 01:04:52,967
<i>如果他能像马一样
把嘴唇贴近点就好了
If he holds his lips together, he
could draw it carefully, like a horse.</i>

857
01:04:53,175 --> 01:04:55,970
<i>-别那麽恶心
-我能把面包沾进去吗?
- Don't be disgusting.
- May I dip my bread in it?</i>

858
01:04:56,178 --> 01:04:59,056
<i>-查莉呢?
-她在准备晚餐
- Where's Charlie?
- She wanted to serve dinner.</i>

859
01:04:59,265 --> 01:05:02,893
<i>-她很快就来
-说得对祖
- She ' II be in in a minute.
- You're right, Joe.</i>

860
01:05:03,102 --> 01:05:06,230
没什麽特别新闻
她来了!
Nothing special tonight. Oh, here she is!

861
01:05:06,439 --> 01:05:09,275
<i>-我可爱的外甥女来了
-我想知道你睡了多久
- Here ' s my girl.
- How many hours did you sleep?</i>

862
01:05:09,483 --> 01:05:12,236
只要你告诉我什麽时候睡
If you could tell me
the exact minute you went to sleep,

863
01:05:12,445 --> 01:05:15,656
你什麽时候醒
如果你中途有醒来...
the exact minute you woke up,
if you woke up in between

864
01:05:15,865 --> 01:05:18,659
那你醒了多久
and how long you stayed awake
each time you woke up,

865
01:05:18,868 --> 01:05:20,619
然後我就能准确告诉你
then I could tell you exactly -

866
01:05:20,828 --> 01:05:24,457
你今晚准睡不著
没人能睡一整天的
You won't sleep tonight.
Nobody who sleeps all day can.

867
01:05:24,665 --> 01:05:27,501
我昨晚做梦
I slept all right, and I kept dreaming,

868
01:05:27,710 --> 01:05:31,422
关于你的噩梦
查理叔叔
perfect nightmares
about you, Uncle Charlie.

869
01:05:31,630 --> 01:05:32,757
关于我的噩梦?
Nightmares about me?

870
01:05:32,965 --> 01:05:38,679
你在火车上
想躲避某些东西...
You were on a train,
running away from something

871
01:05:38,888 --> 01:05:42,391
我很高兴看到你在火车上
and when I saw you on the train,
I felt terribly happy.

872
01:05:42,600 --> 01:05:45,811
<i>看到查理叔叔在
火车上又怎会高兴呢?
How could you feel happy
seeing Uncle Charlie on a train?</i>

873
01:05:46,020 --> 01:05:49,565
我才不要他离开呢
我要他留在这
I don't want to see him on a train.
I hope he stays here forever.

874
01:05:49,774 --> 01:05:54,820
他始终要走
我们要面对现实
Well, he has to leave sometime.
We have to face the facts.

875
01:05:55,029 --> 01:05:57,573
我欣赏面对现实的人
I like people who face facts.

876
01:05:57,782 --> 01:06:01,160
我们也不一定
要遇到那些事
Well, we're not going
to face any such facts as those.

877
01:06:02,703 --> 01:06:05,539
安妮你要看笑话吗?
Oh, Ann,
would you like to see the funnies?

878
01:06:05,748 --> 01:06:10,002
我长大了
一个星期还看两本书
I'm too old for funnies. I read two books
a week. I took a sacred oath I would.

879
01:06:10,211 --> 01:06:13,798
而且在饭桌上
阅读是不礼貌的
Besides, no one's allowed to read
at the table. It isn't polite.

880
01:06:14,006 --> 01:06:15,633
不要顶撞长辈!
Don't correct your elders!

881
01:06:15,841 --> 01:06:17,885
不关她事艾玛
是我忘了
She's right, Emmy.
I'm forgetting my manners.

882
01:06:18,094 --> 01:06:20,971
祖我不是说你带报纸来
Joe, I'm going to blame this paper on you.

883
01:06:21,180 --> 01:06:26,310
罗杰去冰箱
找那红瓶子的酒来
Roger, go to the icebox and bring me
a big, red bottle you'll find there.

884
01:06:26,519 --> 01:06:29,647
现在能把报纸扔走
爸爸读过你也读过
You can throw the paper away.
Dad's read it, you've read it.

885
01:06:29,855 --> 01:06:32,400
今晚我们
也不玩什麽游戏了
We don't need to play any
games with it tonight.

886
01:06:32,608 --> 01:06:35,069
<i>安妮帮查莉
把水果拿出来
Ann, you can help
Charlie carry the vegetables.</i>

887
01:06:35,277 --> 01:06:38,072
<i>我准备晚餐
时就看到那瓶酒
I saw that bottle
when I was getting dinner.</i>

888
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:42,243
圣.波罗说过「
为了胃部著想而喝点酒」
St Paul said, "Take a little wine
for thy stomach's sake. "

889
01:06:42,451 --> 01:06:44,328
餐酒...
听起来多暧昧!
Wine for dinner sounds so gay!

890
01:06:44,537 --> 01:06:49,166
记得老琼斯的大女儿
结婚时的酒吗?
Remember they had the champagne
when the oldest Jones girl got married?

891
01:06:49,375 --> 01:06:50,710
那是正宗
法国勃艮第红酒啊
This is sparkling burgundy.

892
01:06:50,918 --> 01:06:55,423
只要一口
我就知道是勃艮第红酒
One sip and I'll be calling it
"sparkling burgledy. "

893
01:06:55,631 --> 01:06:57,758
<i>我还是不要喝了
Maybe I'd better not take any.</i>

894
01:06:57,967 --> 01:07:00,302
噢...进口的
Oh... imported.

895
01:07:00,511 --> 01:07:03,014
法国进口和那些斜纹?
Imported Frankie and his tweeds?

896
01:07:03,222 --> 01:07:05,266
他把斜纹刻在拐杖上
And his loaded cane.

897
01:07:05,474 --> 01:07:07,560
他把什麽都刻上去!
His loaded everything!

898
01:07:12,857 --> 01:07:17,361
<i>罗杰拿四苹杯子出来
Roger, go get four
of the small glasses with stems.</i>

899
01:07:17,570 --> 01:07:23,159
<i>我答应俱乐部的格林太太
你给女士们演讲
Charles, I promised Mrs Greene of our
club that you'd talk to the ladies.</i>

900
01:07:23,367 --> 01:07:27,955
我讲什麽好呢?
一般都是时事和见闻
What am I going to talk about?
Travel or current events?

901
01:07:28,164 --> 01:07:30,291
<i>不要讲时事
我们听得多了
Oh, not current events.
We get current events.</i>

902
01:07:30,499 --> 01:07:32,543
<i>什麽类型的观众?
Who'll my audience be?</i>

903
01:07:32,752 --> 01:07:36,005
像我一样的家庭主妇
Oh, women like myself.
Busy with our homes, most of us.

904
01:07:36,213 --> 01:07:38,424
<i>这城镇的女士们都很忙
Women keep busy in towns like this.</i>

905
01:07:38,632 --> 01:07:43,846
在大城市就不同
中年的寡妇
In the cities it's different.
Middle-aged widows, husbands dead,

906
01:07:44,055 --> 01:07:48,976
<i>她们死去的丈夫
穷尽一生积累财富
husbands who ' ve spent their lives
making fortunes, working and working,</i>

907
01:07:49,185 --> 01:07:53,397
<i>留下一大笔钱给
愚蠢的妻子
and then they die and leave their money
to their wives, their silly wives.</i>

908
01:07:53,606 --> 01:07:57,193
这些没用的妻子们怎麽做?
And what do the wives do,
these useless women?

909
01:07:57,401 --> 01:08:01,947
她们出入
最豪华奢侈的酒店
You see them in the best hotels
every day by the thousands,

910
01:08:02,156 --> 01:08:04,450
吃喝玩乐
挥霍度日
drinking the money, eating the money,

911
01:08:04,658 --> 01:08:07,703
花钱如流水
losing the money at bridge,
playing all day and all night,

912
01:08:07,912 --> 01:08:09,872
浑身都是铜臭味
smelling of money.

913
01:08:10,081 --> 01:08:13,667
唯一值得引以为荣的
是她们的珠宝
Proud of their jewellery,
but of nothing else.

914
01:08:13,876 --> 01:08:18,506
讨厌衰老肥胖
贪心的女人
Horrible, faded, fat, greedy women.

915
01:08:18,714 --> 01:08:22,051
<i>但她们是人啊!
活生生的人啊!
But they're alive! They're human beings.</i>

916
01:08:22,259 --> 01:08:25,304
是吗?是吗查莉?
Are they? Are they, Charlie?

917
01:08:25,513 --> 01:08:29,725
<i>她们不像贪得
无厌的动物吗?怎麽样?
Are they human,
or are they fat, wheezing animals? Hm?</i>

918
01:08:29,934 --> 01:08:34,230
动物变老
肥得不能动了又怎麽样?
And what happens to animals when
they get too fat and too old?

919
01:08:34,438 --> 01:08:36,982
我好像在这就演讲了
Well, I seem to be making
my speech right here.

920
01:08:37,191 --> 01:08:42,947
不要在俱乐部说这些!
你会被赶下台的
Don't talk about women like that
in front of my club! You'll be lynched.

921
01:08:43,155 --> 01:08:48,160
波特太太也去
她跟我提起你
That nice Mrs Potter's going to be there.
She was asking me about you.

922
01:08:48,369 --> 01:08:53,416
格林把她带去俱乐部
演讲後我帮你介绍
The Greenes are bringing her here to
the party I'm having for you afterwards.

923
01:08:53,708 --> 01:08:55,668
<i>祖贺博来了
Joe, it's Herbert.</i>

924
01:08:55,876 --> 01:08:58,462
他总是在我们吃饭时来
He always comes when we're eating.

925
01:09:00,423 --> 01:09:03,551
<i>晚安牛顿太太
Good evening, Mrs Newton.</i>

926
01:09:03,759 --> 01:09:06,178
-晚安奥克里先生
-晚安
- Good evening, Mr Oakley.
- Good evening.

927
01:09:06,387 --> 01:09:09,056
<i>贺博你妈妈还好吗?
Well, Herb, how's your mother?</i>

928
01:09:09,223 --> 01:09:11,267
噢一般吧
Oh, she's just middling.

929
01:09:12,393 --> 01:09:16,188
-吃饭了吗?
-一小时前吃过了
- Had your dinner?
- Oh, I had mine an hour ago.

930
01:09:16,397 --> 01:09:20,985
你们果然新潮
这麽晚才吃饭啊
You folks are getting pretty stylish.
Having dinner later every evening.

931
01:09:21,193 --> 01:09:23,070
<i>哈哈!
Ha ha!</i>

932
01:09:27,783 --> 01:09:29,702
<i>-祖
-怎麽啦?
- Joe.
- Huh?</i>

933
01:09:29,910 --> 01:09:35,499
-祖我摘了些蘑菇
-你没告诉我
- Joe, I-I picked some mushrooms.
- You don't say?

934
01:09:35,708 --> 01:09:38,377
蘑菇令你想起什麽吗?
Mushrooms mean anything to you, Joe?

935
01:09:38,586 --> 01:09:43,758
我在外面吃的肉排
还不如这个美味呢
I eat 'em on my steak when I'm out
and the meat's not good enough as it is.

936
01:09:43,966 --> 01:09:46,093
我送你些蘑菇
你会吃吗?
If I brought you some mushrooms,
would you eat 'em?

937
01:09:46,302 --> 01:09:48,095
可能会吧
为什麽这样说?
Suppose I would. Why?

938
01:09:48,304 --> 01:09:53,309
对了我最多只会
被判一般杀人罪
Then I've got it. The worst I'd be
accused of would be manslaughter.

939
01:09:53,517 --> 01:09:57,229
造成意外死亡
乾净利落
Doubt if I'd get that.
Accidental death, pure and simple.

940
01:09:57,438 --> 01:10:01,817
一篮子的蘑菇里...
只有两三个有毒
A basket of good mushrooms and...
two or three poisonous ones.

941
01:10:02,026 --> 01:10:06,822
不无知的陪审团
只会注意有毒的
No, no. Innocent party might
get the poisonous ones.

942
01:10:07,031 --> 01:10:09,408
我在刮胡子时想到一方法
I thought of something better
when I was shaving.

943
01:10:09,617 --> 01:10:14,705
浴盆把你倒挂著
而你的腿放在外面
这有人做过了但兵不厌诈
A bath tub. Pull the legs out
from under you, hold you down.

944
01:10:17,583 --> 01:10:19,502
<i>你们怎麽了?
Oh, what's the matter with you two?</i>

945
01:10:19,710 --> 01:10:22,171
非得整天都说著杀人吗?
Do you always have to
talk about killing people?

946
01:10:22,380 --> 01:10:24,340
我们不是说杀其他人
We're not talking about killing people.

947
01:10:24,548 --> 01:10:27,510
贺博想杀我
而我想杀他
Herb's talking about killing me,
and I'm talking about killing him.

948
01:10:27,718 --> 01:10:29,637
这是你爸爸的娱乐方式
It's your father's way of relaxing.

949
01:10:29,845 --> 01:10:31,931
他就不能用其他方式吗?
Can't he find some other way to relax?

950
01:10:32,139 --> 01:10:36,769
除了研究毒药
就不能有点安宁吗?
Can't we have a little peace and quiet
without dragging in poisons all the time?

951
01:10:36,977 --> 01:10:39,939
<i>查莉!她在胡说八道
Charlie!
She doesn ' t make sense talking like that.</i>

952
01:10:40,147 --> 01:10:42,441
<i>真令人担心罗杰
找她回来
I'm worried about her.
Roger, bring her back.</i>

953
01:10:42,650 --> 01:10:46,737
我跟著她
你们继续吃
I'll go. You stay and finish dinner.
I'll catch up with her.

954
01:10:46,946 --> 01:10:49,490
<i>她怎麽了?
What's wrong with her?</i>

955
01:11:01,377 --> 01:11:05,464
-对不起诺顿警官
-你总是在街上乱跑
- Excuse me, Mr Norton.
- You're always running around at night.

956
01:11:05,673 --> 01:11:09,427
-你昨晚匆匆忙忙去哪?
-只是有点事做
- Where were you hurrying to last night?
- Just doing an errand.

957
01:11:09,635 --> 01:11:12,888
-这位是你的叔叔吗?
-是的
- Is this your uncle I've heard about?
- Yes.

958
01:11:13,097 --> 01:11:16,350
-诺顿警官这是查理叔叔
-很高兴认识你你叫?
- Uncle Charlie, Mr Norton.
- Glad to know you. What's the name?

959
01:11:16,559 --> 01:11:18,811
查理.奥克里
很高兴认识你
Oakley. Charles Oakley. Nice to meet you.

960
01:11:19,020 --> 01:11:23,357
管好你的外甥女
下次我可要给她开罚单
Better keep your eye on your niece.
I'll have to give her a ticket for speeding.

961
01:11:23,566 --> 01:11:26,819
在马路上横冲直撞
是违法的知道吗?
- City ordinance about running.
- Hear that, Charlie?

962
01:11:27,028 --> 01:11:29,530
不要知法犯法
我会看好她的了
Don't want to break the law.
I'll take care of her.

963
01:11:29,739 --> 01:11:32,033
晚安
- Good night.
- Good night.

964
01:11:32,241 --> 01:11:35,453
查莉怎麽了?
发生什麽事了?
What's the matter, Charlie?
What's wrong?

965
01:11:45,087 --> 01:11:47,673
-我要跟你谈谈
-你又弄痛我了
- I want to talk to you.
- You're hurting my arm again.

966
01:11:47,882 --> 01:11:50,843
-跟我来
-不我没来过这些地方
- Come in here with me.
- I can't. I don't go to places like this.

967
01:11:51,052 --> 01:11:53,095
来
Go on in.

968
01:12:06,400 --> 01:12:09,195
-带我来这干嘛?
-在哪里又有什麽关系呢?
- Why'd you bring me here?
- What does it matter where we are?

969
01:12:09,403 --> 01:12:11,197
-你好查莉
-你好
Hello, Charlie. Hello.

970
01:12:11,405 --> 01:12:15,409
路易斯你好查理叔叔
这是路易斯.菲治你好
Hello, Louise.
Uncle Charlie, Louise Finch.

971
01:12:15,618 --> 01:12:20,122
-这是我的叔叔
-我是查莉的同学
- This is my uncle.
- I was in Charlie's class in school.

972
01:12:20,331 --> 01:12:24,418
没想过你会来这里
I sure was surprised to see you come in.
I never thought I'd see you here.

973
01:12:24,627 --> 01:12:28,547
我来这里有两周了
I been here two weeks.
Lost my job over at Kern's.

974
01:12:28,756 --> 01:12:32,635
我在全镇一半的酒吧干过
要点什麽?
I've been in half the restaurants in town.
What'll you have, Charlie?

975
01:12:32,843 --> 01:12:38,057
不了给她一杯
姜汁我要白兰地
- Nothing, thank you.
- A ginger ale for her, a brandy for me.

976
01:12:38,265 --> 01:12:41,727
-查莉怎麽了
-怎麽了?
- Well, Charlie?
- Well?

977
01:12:41,936 --> 01:12:45,898
你知道很多吗?
那家伙告诉你些东西
Think you know something, don't you?
That young fellow told you something.

978
01:12:46,107 --> 01:12:48,859
杰克?凭什麽说
他知道你的事?
Jack?
Why should he know anything about you?

979
01:12:50,486 --> 01:12:56,242
-查莉我不想
我们之间有什麽误会
Charlie, something's come between us.
I don't want that to happen.

980
01:12:56,450 --> 01:12:59,203
因为我们是老朋友啊
而且...
Why, we're old friends.

981
01:13:00,287 --> 01:13:04,417
我们就像双胞胎
More than that. We're like twins.

982
01:13:04,625 --> 01:13:07,878
-是你自己说
-查理叔叔别碰我
- You said so yourself.
- Don't touch me, Uncle Charlie.

983
01:13:10,589 --> 01:13:12,383
他跟你说了什麽?
What did that boy tell you?

984
01:13:12,591 --> 01:13:19,056
他没说什麽
我也想他不知道你的事
He's got nothing to do with it. I hope
he never knows anything about you.

985
01:13:19,265 --> 01:13:24,270
查莉
你真是细心可爱的女孩
Charlie,
you're a pretty understanding sort of girl.

986
01:13:27,273 --> 01:13:29,942
如果你听到
关于我的传闻
If you've heard
some little things about me,

987
01:13:30,109 --> 01:13:34,780
我想你肯定
不会把它当真
I guess you're a woman of the world
enough to overlook them.

988
01:13:37,408 --> 01:13:41,662
人人都看出
你是家里的支柱
You're the head of your family, Charlie.
Anyone can see that.

989
01:13:41,871 --> 01:13:47,418
我老了我十六岁
就开始到处漂泊
I'm not so old. I've been chasing
around the globe since I was sixteen.

990
01:13:49,462 --> 01:13:51,839
<i>我做了些蠢事
I guess I've done
some pretty foolish things,</i>

991
01:13:52,048 --> 01:13:54,550
犯了愚蠢的错误
made some pretty foolish mistakes.

992
01:13:54,759 --> 01:13:58,471
<i>没什麽大不了
只是...可笑的错误
Nothing serious, just... foolish.</i>

993
01:14:15,279 --> 01:14:19,158
查莉别妄自猜测
Oh, Charlie, now,
don't start imagining things.

994
01:14:19,367 --> 01:14:24,538
你怎麽能做出这种事?
你是我的叔叔
How could you do such things?
You're my uncle,

995
01:14:24,747 --> 01:14:26,457
<i>我妈的弟弟
my mother's brother.</i>

996
01:14:26,665 --> 01:14:30,378
我们都认为
你是很成功的人
We thought you were
the most wonderful man in the world.

997
01:14:30,586 --> 01:14:34,173
-世界上最成功的人
-查莉你知道什麽?
- The most wonderful and the best.
- Charlie, what do you know?

998
01:14:43,140 --> 01:14:45,810
让你们久等了
我们真的很忙
I'm sorry I was so long.
We're awful busy.

999
01:14:48,020 --> 01:14:51,357
这是谁的?
不是很漂亮吗?
Whose is it? Ain't it beautiful?

1000
01:14:53,734 --> 01:14:56,404
我一直都想
拥有这样的戒指
I'd just die for a ring like that.

1001
01:14:56,654 --> 01:15:00,491
这戒指简直让我目眩
Yes sir, for a ring like that,
I'd just about die.

1002
01:15:00,700 --> 01:15:03,953
我最爱珠宝--真的珠宝
I love jewellery, real jewellery.

1003
01:15:04,161 --> 01:15:08,708
我根本不用就能辩出真假
Notice I didn't even have to ask
if it was real. You can tell.

1004
01:15:08,916 --> 01:15:11,669
-我知道
-我要多一杯白兰地
- I can.
- Bring me another brandy.

1005
01:15:13,504 --> 01:15:15,631
坐下
Sit down.

1006
01:15:15,840 --> 01:15:17,883
坐下!
Sit down!

1007
01:15:21,721 --> 01:15:24,807
你认为自己知道多少?
You think you know something,
don't you?

1008
01:15:25,016 --> 01:15:28,019
你以为你很聪明
You think you're the clever little girl
who knows something.

1009
01:15:28,227 --> 01:15:32,023
但你不知道的还多著呢
There's so much you don't know.
So much.

1010
01:15:32,231 --> 01:15:33,899
你知道什麽?
What do you know, really?

1011
01:15:34,108 --> 01:15:38,029
你只不过是个普通的女孩
You're just an ordinary little girl
living in an ordinary little town.

1012
01:15:38,237 --> 01:15:42,366
每天从床上醒来
无　无虑
You wake up every day and know there's
nothing in the world to trouble you.

1013
01:15:42,575 --> 01:15:45,244
平平淡淡地过日子...
You go through your ordinary little day.

1014
01:15:45,411 --> 01:15:51,250
晚上睡在安稳的床
做些无聊的梦
At night, you sleep your ordinary sleep
filled with peaceful, stupid dreams.

1015
01:15:52,835 --> 01:15:55,212
是我给你带来噩梦
And I brought you nightmares.

1016
01:15:56,839 --> 01:16:00,301
对吗?还是一个谎言?
Or did I?
Or was it a silly, inexpert, little lie?

1017
01:16:00,509 --> 01:16:03,804
你生活在梦境里
看不到现实
You live in a dream.
You're a sleepwalker, blind.

1018
01:16:04,013 --> 01:16:06,474
你知道外面的世界是怎样吗?
How do you know
what the world is like?

1019
01:16:06,682 --> 01:16:09,560
你能想像那就像
猪圈般肮脏吗?
Do you know the world is a foul sty?

1020
01:16:09,769 --> 01:16:14,190
<i>你知道周围是带著
面具的卑贱小人吗?
Do you know if you ripped
the fronts off houses, you'd find swine?</i>

1021
01:16:14,398 --> 01:16:16,734
这个该死的世界
有谁在乎发生什麽?
The world's a hell.
What does it matter what happens in it?

1022
01:16:16,942 --> 01:16:20,488
<i>醒醒吧查莉
你的聪明去哪了?
Wake up, Charlie.
Use your wits. Learn something!</i>

1023
01:16:20,696 --> 01:16:22,573
查莉你走了吗?
You goin', Charlie?

1024
01:16:42,677 --> 01:16:45,596
-查莉你会帮我吗?
-帮你?
- Charlie, will you help me?
- Help you?

1025
01:16:45,805 --> 01:16:51,143
我们身上淌著一样的血
一周前我几乎绝望
The same blood flows through our veins.
I was at the end of my rope.

1026
01:16:52,645 --> 01:16:56,941
我太累了我受够了
Oh, I'm so tired. There's an end
to the running a man can do.

1027
01:16:57,149 --> 01:17:00,986
你没法想像那种累
我准备--
You'll never know what it's like
to be so tired. I was going to...

1028
01:17:03,364 --> 01:17:09,161
嗯...我想离开这里
帮帮我查莉
Then I got the idea of coming out here.
It's my last chance, Charlie.

1029
01:17:09,870 --> 01:17:11,914
给我一次机会
Give it to me.

1030
01:17:12,998 --> 01:17:14,917
格翰和那个家伙不知道
Graham and the other fellow,
they don't know.

1031
01:17:15,126 --> 01:17:19,130
如果抓到东部的那个
嫌疑犯我就--
There's a man in the east they suspect,
and if they get him, I'll...

1032
01:17:19,338 --> 01:17:22,800
查莉给我一次机会
Charlie, give me this last chance.

1033
01:17:23,009 --> 01:17:25,428
好吧那你走!
Take your chance. Go!

1034
01:17:25,636 --> 01:17:28,389
我会走的查莉
给我几天时间
I'll go, Charlie. Just give me a few days.

1035
01:17:28,597 --> 01:17:31,100
为你妈妈著想
她知道後会疯的
Think of your mother.
It'll kill your mother.

1036
01:17:31,308 --> 01:17:34,562
我知道她会受不了的
Yes, it would kill my mother.

1037
01:17:34,770 --> 01:17:38,024
那你几天後要离开这里
Take your few days.
See that you get away from here.

1038
01:17:38,232 --> 01:17:41,360
你知道如果
我被抓了後果是什麽?
You realise what it'll mean
if they get me?

1039
01:17:41,569 --> 01:17:43,529
坐电椅
The electric chair.

1040
01:17:43,738 --> 01:17:47,241
查莉全靠你了
你要帮我啊
Charlie, you've got to help me.

1041
01:17:47,450 --> 01:17:52,621
你说我们不仅是叔叔
与外甥女关系
You said yourself we're no ordinary uncle
and niece, no matter what I've done.

1042
01:17:52,830 --> 01:17:56,042
你先进去我跟著来
You go in. I'll be in in a minute.

1043
01:18:10,765 --> 01:18:13,476
<i>-家是最好的地方
-查莉呢?
- Home, sweet home.
- Where's Charlie?</i>

1044
01:18:13,684 --> 01:18:16,562
<i>-她在外面别担心
-她怎麽了?
- She's outside. Don't worry about her.
- What was the matter?</i>

1045
01:18:16,771 --> 01:18:21,150
<i>她有点烦躁
我让她去散散心
She was a little edgy. I persuaded her
to go for a walk. She's calmer now.</i>

1046
01:18:21,359 --> 01:18:26,614
<i>-那就好给你留了甜品
-冰淇淋苏打
- I'm so glad. I've saved dessert for you.
- We had an ice-cream soda.</i>

1047
01:18:26,822 --> 01:18:31,827
噢!你快点上床吧!
Oops-a-daisy! Off to bed you go!

1048
01:18:55,101 --> 01:18:57,770
<i>-罗杰过来!
-不!
- Roger, come here!
- No!</i>

1049
01:19:02,441 --> 01:19:06,070
我来对付她
嘘!安妮!
There's my girl. Psst! Ann!

1050
01:19:06,278 --> 01:19:09,323
你好!
你一定是藏著什麽
Hello!
You must be trying to hide or something.

1051
01:19:09,532 --> 01:19:13,577
-我没有
-只有藏著东西的人才会说嘘
- We're not hiding.
- People who are hiding say "psst".

1052
01:19:13,786 --> 01:19:16,372
-我不想在星期天吵闹
-听著安妮
- We just don't want to yell on Sunday.
- Look, Ann.

1053
01:19:16,580 --> 01:19:21,210
叫你姐姐来一下
小声点我们在这等
Ask your sister to run over here.
Just ask her quietly. We'll wait here.

1054
01:19:21,419 --> 01:19:24,922
-我爸爸跟你爸爸有过节吗?
-我爸爸?
- Did my father have a feud with yours?
- My father?

1055
01:19:25,131 --> 01:19:29,093
不然你不会
瞒著别人叫她来
Because if they didn't, there's no sense
in my asking Charlotte quietly.

1056
01:19:29,301 --> 01:19:32,763
妈妈不介意的
她说女人就该生儿育女
Mama won't care. She thinks
girls ought to marry and settle down.

1057
01:19:32,972 --> 01:19:35,433
-我读过一本书--
-叫她来吧别卖弄文才了
- In a book I'm reading -
- Just ask her, Ann. Don't be literary.

1058
01:19:35,641 --> 01:19:38,477
-好吧
-记住由我来说
- Alright.
- Remember, I'm doing all the talking.

1059
01:19:45,526 --> 01:19:47,153
<i>-你好
-你好你好凯瑟琳
- Hello.
- Hello.</i>

1060
01:19:47,361 --> 01:19:49,697
早\'上好格翰警官
Good morning, Mr Graham.

1061
01:19:49,905 --> 01:19:52,867
凯瑟琳
这是桑德斯警官
Catherine, this is Mr Saunders.

1062
01:19:53,075 --> 01:19:55,411
-你好
-你好
- How do you do?
- How do you do?

1063
01:19:55,619 --> 01:19:58,998
-安妮说你有事找我
-桑德斯有事跟你说
- Ann says you want to speak to me.
- Saunders wants to.

1064
01:19:59,206 --> 01:20:02,668
来安妮，跟凯瑟琳说说吧
Come on, Ann.
Tell Catherine the story of Dracula.

1065
01:20:02,877 --> 01:20:04,920
来吧，凯瑟琳
Come on, Catherine.

1066
01:20:06,756 --> 01:20:10,968
-你想怎样?
-让他们走远点再说
- What do you want?
- Let them get a little bit ahead.

1067
01:20:16,515 --> 01:20:20,644
我想说关于
你叔叔的照片的事
It's about that photograph we took,
the one of your uncle.

1068
01:20:20,853 --> 01:20:24,190
-你给回他了他也许烧掉
-不是那张
- He probably burned it.
- Not that one, he hasn't.

1069
01:20:24,398 --> 01:20:26,609
我们给了张错误的相片
We gave him the wrong film.

1070
01:20:26,817 --> 01:20:29,028
我们拿真正的照片
跟东部那边联系
We got the picture alright.
We wired it East.

1071
01:20:29,236 --> 01:20:32,156
那里的证人能认出
谁是我们通缉的罪犯
They've got witnesses can identify
the man we want from that picture.

1072
01:20:32,365 --> 01:20:34,742
-什麽能认出是他?
-对了
- What do you mean, identify him?
- Just what I said.

1073
01:20:34,950 --> 01:20:38,120
当证人看到照片
就能知道他是否罪犯
When the witnesses see that picture,
we'll know whether Oakley's the man.

1074
01:20:38,329 --> 01:20:41,332
-我们准备跟那边联系
-那查理叔叔会--
- We're waiting for the wire now.
- And then Uncle Charlie will be -

1075
01:20:41,540 --> 01:20:44,835
对了就是这样
That's right. That's the way it is.

1076
01:20:47,505 --> 01:20:52,468
格翰想你可以让他离开
这会好点--
Graham thought you could get your uncle
to leave town now. It would be better -

1077
01:20:52,677 --> 01:20:55,971
我会的一定会!
你能给多长时间?
I've got to, haven't I? I've got to!
What's the most time you'll give me?

1078
01:20:56,597 --> 01:21:00,101
两小时内
我会叫他离开的!
- Two hours.
- I'll make him leave!

1079
01:21:00,309 --> 01:21:03,020
你为什麽肯定
他是我们要找的人?
You seem pretty sure
he's the man we want. Why?

1080
01:21:03,229 --> 01:21:07,692
-没有原因我只是害怕
-你是唯一能肯定的人
No reason why. I'm just scared.
You're the ones who seem sure.

1081
01:21:07,900 --> 01:21:12,488
-我不能让这里有事
-你知道他干过什麽?
- I couldn't bear anything happening here.
- You know what he's done?

1082
01:21:12,697 --> 01:21:15,157
-不我不想听!
-希望你知道
- No, I don't want to hear!
- Well, I want you to get this.

1083
01:21:15,366 --> 01:21:20,621
我们想帮你
把知道的都告诉我们吧!
We're doing you a favour. If you know
anything more about your uncle, tell us.

1084
01:21:20,830 --> 01:21:23,124
我们还想知道
他什麽时候离开
We also want to know
when and how he leaves town.

1085
01:21:23,332 --> 01:21:24,875
-如果你瞒著我们--
-不我会告诉你的
- If you hold out on us -
- I won't. I'll tell you.

1086
01:21:27,795 --> 01:21:30,756
走多一步
你会弄伤妈妈的背
Step on a crack,
you'll break your mother's back.

1087
01:21:30,965 --> 01:21:33,509
我们都想相信你
I wish I knew we could trust you.

1088
01:21:33,718 --> 01:21:36,762
我保证不会再帮他了
I won't do anything to help him,
I promise.

1089
01:21:36,971 --> 01:21:40,016
但你不能让
我去暗中监视他
But you can't ask me to spy on him.

1090
01:21:40,224 --> 01:21:43,853
我们来个交易
我叫他离开
We've made a bargain.
I'll get him to leave. That's all I'll do.

1091
01:21:44,061 --> 01:21:46,731
查莉他是危险人物
一旦离开我们视线范围--
Think, Charlie. The man's dangerous.
If he gets away from us -

1092
01:21:46,939 --> 01:21:51,986
我不想知道他做什麽
我会遵守诺言
I don't want to hear what he'll do.
We've made a bargain. I'll keep it.

1093
01:21:52,194 --> 01:21:54,697
他走的时候
我会通知你
I'll let you know when he leaves.

1094
01:21:54,905 --> 01:21:59,869
万一他不是通缉犯
那有好看的
Funny if he turned out
to be the wrong man. Could be.

1095
01:22:00,077 --> 01:22:03,914
<i>-安妮
-我把妈妈的背弄伤了三次
- Ann!
- I broke my mother's back three times.</i>

1096
01:22:04,123 --> 01:22:08,210
你还没说罗斯小姐
是否嫁给了有钱人...
Not bad. You didn't finish telling me
whether Miss Rose married the rich guy,

1097
01:22:08,419 --> 01:22:11,339
-或者她的新欢
-你跟她那麽熟啊?
- or the one she was in love with.
- How long have you two such friends?

1098
01:22:11,547 --> 01:22:15,092
我们在玩游戏
我问她答
Oh, we play games. I ask questions.
She knows all the answers.

1099
01:22:15,384 --> 01:22:18,220
<i>麻烦的是
我弄不懂她在胡扯什麽
The only trouble is
I can't make out what she's making up.</i>

1100
01:22:18,429 --> 01:22:21,724
我不会胡扯，说的都是书本上的知识
I never make up anything.
I get everything from my books.

1101
01:22:21,932 --> 01:22:23,434
我说的都是事实
They're all true.

1102
01:22:23,642 --> 01:22:27,563
安妮来吧
我们去帮忙做饭吧再见
Come on, Ann. We'd better get home
and help with dinner. Goodbye.

1103
01:22:27,772 --> 01:22:31,233
再见再见
格翰警官桑德斯警官
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye, Mr Graham. Mr Saunders.

1104
01:22:31,442 --> 01:22:33,486
<i>-再见凯瑟琳
-再见
- Goodbye, Catherine.
- Come on, Catherine.</i>

1105
01:22:33,694 --> 01:22:38,074
为啥不去摘些花
点缀一下晚餐?越简单越好
- Why not pick flowers for the table?
- Simple flowers are the best.

1106
01:22:38,282 --> 01:22:41,660
<i>-不用是紫罗兰的
-要是我在南方出生就好了
- I didn't ask for orchids.
- I wish I'd been born in the South.</i>

1107
01:22:41,869 --> 01:22:45,164
<i>南方的女人很有魅力
她们戴著手套摘花
Southern women have a lot of charm.
They pick flowers with gloves on.</i>

1108
01:22:45,373 --> 01:22:47,875
-再见凯瑟琳
-再见查莉晚饭後见
- Goodbye, Catherine.
- Goodbye, Charlie. See you after dinner.

1109
01:22:48,084 --> 01:22:49,752
再见
Bye.

1110
01:22:50,670 --> 01:22:52,963
<i>-安妮你好
-你好
- Hello, Ann.
- Hello.</i>

1111
01:22:53,172 --> 01:22:57,968
教堂怎麽样?
够座位吗?有人要让座吗?
How was church, Charlie? Did you
count the house? Turn anybody away?

1112
01:22:58,177 --> 01:23:00,471
不够了
No, room enough for everyone.

1113
01:23:00,680 --> 01:23:02,682
很好
I'm glad to hear that.

1114
01:23:02,890 --> 01:23:07,103
演出一段时间了
观众会陆续减少
Show's been running such a long time,
I thought attendance might be falling off.

1115
01:23:07,311 --> 01:23:09,855
<i>电台有什麽新闻吗?
Anything special on the noon broadcast?</i>

1116
01:23:10,064 --> 01:23:14,318
说抓到了另一个
嫌疑犯--玛丽寡妇杀手
They caught that other fellow,
the Merry Widow Murderer.

1117
01:23:14,527 --> 01:23:17,697
<i>-真的吗?哪里?
-缅因州的波特兰
- They did, did they? Where?
- State of Maine. Portland.</i>

1118
01:23:17,905 --> 01:23:21,242
不算真正的抓到
他逃避警方的追捕
Didn't catch him exactly.
He was running away from the police,

1119
01:23:21,450 --> 01:23:25,871
跑进了飞机场
躲到飞机的推进器後
and they cornered him at the airport
and he ran into the propeller of a plane.

1120
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:27,915
-噢!
-他被切得肢离破碎
- Oh, boy!
- Cut him all to pieces.

1121
01:23:28,124 --> 01:23:30,376
只能从衣服辩认
Had to identify him by his clothes.

1122
01:23:30,584 --> 01:23:34,505
他的衣服印著「C」「O」
省略号「H」
His shirts were all initialled,
"C," "O," apostrophe "H."

1123
01:23:34,714 --> 01:23:37,174
很快就能划上句号的了
Well, makes a good ending.
Couldn't have done better myself.

1124
01:23:37,383 --> 01:23:39,593
这案子很快就结束的
I guess that closes that case pretty final.

1125
01:23:39,802 --> 01:23:43,014
<i>当然不用太担心那案子
Sure does.
Never cared much for that case.</i>

1126
01:23:43,222 --> 01:23:48,769
我今天可要饱餐一顿啦
Well, I think I'll go get ready for dinner.
I'm hungry. I can eat a good dinner today.

1127
01:24:47,119 --> 01:24:51,248
查莉有好消息通知你
哪里能聊几句?
Charlie, I have great news for you.
Where can we talk alone?

1128
01:25:02,343 --> 01:25:07,682
缅因州通知结束案子
你也能解脱了
We got a wire from Maine. We can call
off the job. I'll bet you're relieved. I am.

1129
01:25:07,848 --> 01:25:09,600
噢解脱了
Oh, I am relieved.

1130
01:25:09,809 --> 01:25:13,354
<i>还游说你叔叔离开这
他肯定说你疯了
You were trying to get youruncle out.
He must have thought you were crazy.</i>

1131
01:25:13,562 --> 01:25:16,649
一切都结束了
我不想再提了
Now that it's over, I don't
want to talk about it any more.

1132
01:25:16,857 --> 01:25:19,443
我希望假装
这一切没发生过
I'd like to pretend the whole
dreadful thing never happened.

1133
01:25:19,652 --> 01:25:23,781
<i>-你不需要假装啊
-妈妈的手套
- There's nothing to pretend about.
- There's mother's gloves.</i>

1134
01:25:23,989 --> 01:25:26,909
她总是丢三落四的
Mother and her gloves.
She's always losing things.

1135
01:25:27,118 --> 01:25:30,371
<i>迟早\'她连你也会失去的
All mothers lose things.
Someday, she'll be losing you.</i>

1136
01:25:30,579 --> 01:25:34,250
她才没有损失呢
还多了一个女婿
Mothers don't lose daughters,
they gain sons.

1137
01:25:34,458 --> 01:25:37,795
也是但事情
总不那麽如意譬如我吧
Yes, but gain isn't always the word.
Now, take me.

1138
01:25:38,004 --> 01:25:40,423
谁想要个侦探做女婿?
Who'd want a detective
for a son-in-law?

1139
01:25:40,631 --> 01:25:42,758
-我爸爸会
-他会?
- My father would.
- He would?

1140
01:25:42,967 --> 01:25:48,222
如果你说要嫁给侦探
他会怎麽反应?
If you told him you were going to marry
a detective, he wouldn't disown you?

1141
01:25:48,431 --> 01:25:50,307
不一定是我啊
可以是安妮
It wouldn't have to be me. There's Ann.

1142
01:25:50,516 --> 01:25:54,687
不她跟我说要
嫁给图书管理员
No, Ann wants to marry a librarian.
She told me.

1143
01:25:54,895 --> 01:25:58,649
所以她经常读那麽多书
So she'll always have
plenty of books around to read.

1144
01:26:00,609 --> 01:26:02,486
什麽事了?
What's the matter?

1145
01:26:02,695 --> 01:26:06,282
我好久没这麽开怀地笑了
I was laughing.
It's been so long since I laughed.

1146
01:26:06,490 --> 01:26:08,159
我喜欢你笑的样子
I like it when you laugh.

1147
01:26:08,367 --> 01:26:13,581
我喜欢你做的每件事
I like it when you don't.
I guess I like you whatever you do.

1148
01:26:13,789 --> 01:26:18,210
-我喜欢你
-我也喜欢你
- I guess I like you.
- I'm glad. I like you too.

1149
01:26:18,419 --> 01:26:23,591
有趣的是你遇见一个人
然後...爱上她
Funny how you happen to meet someone
and like them and... like them.

1150
01:26:23,799 --> 01:26:25,634
嗯
Mm-hm.

1151
01:26:25,843 --> 01:26:27,595
-查莉?
-什麽事?
- Charlie?
- Yes?

1152
01:26:27,803 --> 01:26:32,350
我想有天你会
跟你爸爸说--
I suppose it couldn't ever really happen
some day that you'd tell your father...

1153
01:26:32,558 --> 01:26:36,270
要嫁给一个侦探
You know, about marrying someone,
a detective, I mean.

1154
01:26:36,479 --> 01:26:39,690
-我不知道
-我也不想现在告诉你
- I don't know.
- I didn't mean to tell you.

1155
01:26:39,899 --> 01:26:43,152
我想等你把这一切
不愉快的事忘记
I wanted to wait until you'd forgotten
the mess we've been through together,

1156
01:26:43,361 --> 01:26:46,322
直到你想起
我不再有恐惧和不安
till you didn't think of me as part
of something unpleasant and frightening.

1157
01:26:46,530 --> 01:26:50,993
我希望能回来告诉你
I wanted to wait and come back
and then tell you.

1158
01:26:51,202 --> 01:26:53,454
但我想现在就跟你说
But I can't help it.
I want to tell you now.

1159
01:26:53,662 --> 01:26:57,208
查莉我爱你
I love you, Charlie. I love you terribly.

1160
01:26:57,416 --> 01:27:01,545
你介意我现在才说吗?
I know it's no time to tell you now
and I'm sorry. Do you mind?

1161
01:27:01,754 --> 01:27:04,548
-我不介意
-你会考虑一下吗?
- I don't mind.
- Do you think you could think about it?

1162
01:27:04,757 --> 01:27:08,969
-关于你爱我?
-也许你也爱我
- About your loving me?
- And perhaps your loving me?

1163
01:27:10,721 --> 01:27:15,851
我希望保持朋友关系
我们是朋友
I- I'd like us to be friends. I know that.
We are friends.

1164
01:27:16,060 --> 01:27:19,605
-我想保持现状
-没有其他吗?
- I'd like to have that to think about.
- Nothing more?

1165
01:27:19,814 --> 01:27:24,026
我不知道杰克
我...还不知道
I don't know, Jack.
I... just don't know yet.

1166
01:27:24,235 --> 01:27:27,321
好吧
但我能回来看你吗?
Alright. But I may come back?

1167
01:27:27,530 --> 01:27:32,076
噢当然能一定要回啊
Oh, please come back.
Please come back.

1168
01:27:33,119 --> 01:27:34,912
听著查莉
Listen, Charlie.

1169
01:27:35,121 --> 01:27:37,707
我去到市中心的广场
When I go, go back to that square
in the middle of town.

1170
01:27:37,915 --> 01:27:41,544
那是我们初次认识的地方
Take a good look at it.
That's where I first knew I loved you.

1171
01:27:41,752 --> 01:27:45,631
真是不打不相识
That's where we had the fight
and I didn't know what to do.

1172
01:27:45,840 --> 01:27:48,759
我热爱我的工作
只是那晚不喜欢
I like my job,
but I didn't like it that night.

1173
01:27:48,968 --> 01:27:50,928
那晚我讨厌它
I hated it that night.

1174
01:27:51,137 --> 01:27:54,223
-你现在讨厌它吗?
-不
- You hate it now?
- No, not now.

1175
01:27:56,017 --> 01:28:00,730
这像口井
我要弄个装饰品上去
You know, this is a swell place.
I'm going to put a bronze plaque up.

1176
01:28:02,940 --> 01:28:06,068
这门老是自己锁上!
That door's always banging shut!

1177
01:28:06,277 --> 01:28:08,946
噢!大力点!
Oh! It sticks.

1178
01:28:09,989 --> 01:28:11,657
啊!
Uh!

1179
01:28:22,001 --> 01:28:24,879
你们把自己锁在车房干嘛?
What are you two locking yourselves
in the garage for?

1180
01:28:25,087 --> 01:28:27,256
-我年轻的时候是在会议室
-奥克里先生
- When I was young, it was the parlour.
- Hello, Mr Oakley.

1181
01:28:27,465 --> 01:28:29,800
-我在跟查莉说再见
-在车房里?
- I was saying goodbye to Charlie.
- In the garage?

1182
01:28:30,009 --> 01:28:33,179
门被锁上了
现在我也要跟你说再见了
The door got stuck.
Now I'll have to say goodbye to you.

1183
01:28:33,387 --> 01:28:37,475
我们在草坪上道别好了
不用回到车房
Let's say goodbye out here on the lawn.
No use taking a chance on the garage.

1184
01:28:37,683 --> 01:28:40,644
-完了吗?
-完了我会再回来的
- Finished here?
- All finished, but I'll be back.

1185
01:28:40,853 --> 01:28:43,230
<i>-很快就见到我的
-噢?
- You ' II be seeing me around.
- Oh?</i>

1186
01:28:43,439 --> 01:28:45,691
<i>不是因为公事
Not on business, though.</i>

1187
01:28:45,900 --> 01:28:49,904
我明白
查莉是一个好女孩
I can understand you coming back.
Charlie's a fine girl.

1188
01:28:50,112 --> 01:28:52,531
她是我见过最好的女孩
She's the thing I love most in the world.

1189
01:28:52,740 --> 01:28:55,993
说真的格翰警官
一帆风顺
I mean it. Have a nice trip, Mr Graham.

1190
01:28:56,202 --> 01:28:59,288
下次不要乱拍照了
And don't take any more photographs
without permission.

1191
01:28:59,497 --> 01:29:01,791
你知道这是人权啊?
Rights of man. You know, freedom?

1192
01:29:01,999 --> 01:29:05,711
我们下次再讨论这个吧
We'll have a talk
about freedom some day, Mr Oakley.

1193
01:29:11,217 --> 01:29:12,968
-再会
-再会
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

1194
01:29:15,221 --> 01:29:20,226
-记得给我写信
你有我地址吧-嗯
Don't forget to write.
Remember, you have the addresses.

1195
01:29:27,233 --> 01:29:29,276
杰克!
Jack!

1196
01:30:03,310 --> 01:30:08,024
还有吗?牛油水果
蔬菜还要去图书馆
Anything else? I've got butter, fruit,
green thread and go to the library.

1197
01:30:08,232 --> 01:30:12,486
买些新鲜的
如果还有我会叫安妮去
And whatever vegetable looks freshest.
If I've forgotten anything, I'll send Ann.

1198
01:30:12,695 --> 01:30:14,488
好的
Alright.

1199
01:30:19,660 --> 01:30:21,412
妈妈!
Mother!

1200
01:30:21,620 --> 01:30:24,373
查莉!亲爱的!
你没事吧?
Charlie! Darling! Are you hurt?

1201
01:30:25,124 --> 01:30:26,792
我绊倒了
I tripped.

1202
01:30:27,001 --> 01:30:29,545
在哪里?弄伤了膝盖吗?
Oh, what is it? Is it your ankle?

1203
01:30:29,754 --> 01:30:32,673
没什麽事
我扶住了栏杆
I don't think I'm hurt.
I grabbed the banister.

1204
01:30:32,882 --> 01:30:34,383
噢你差点没命了!
You might have been killed!

1205
01:30:35,634 --> 01:30:39,764
<i>每次孩子们走这楼梯
我都很担心
I worry myself sick every time
one of you comes down these stairs.</i>

1206
01:30:39,972 --> 01:30:42,808
<i>太陡峭和有点摇摆
要去修理一下
They're too steep and rickety.
They ought to be fixed.</i>

1207
01:30:43,017 --> 01:30:45,186
<i>你真的没事?
Are you sure you're all right?</i>

1208
01:31:26,310 --> 01:31:28,104
查理叔叔
你什麽时候走?
When are you leaving, Uncle Charlie?

1209
01:31:28,312 --> 01:31:32,441
查莉一切都结束了
我想忘记它
Oh, come now. That other business,
it's all over. I'd like to forget it.

1210
01:31:32,650 --> 01:31:35,319
-我们现在很开心啊
-你什麽时候走?
- We're all happy here.
- When are you leaving?

1211
01:31:35,528 --> 01:31:37,571
我不会走的
I'm not going, you see.

1212
01:31:38,698 --> 01:31:40,866
暂时还不会
Not yet. I'm not going.

1213
01:31:41,075 --> 01:31:44,996
我想在一个熟悉的环境里
安定下来
I want to settle down. Live somewhere
people know me. Put some money by.

1214
01:31:45,204 --> 01:31:49,667
而且成为这个家的一分子
- Start a business. Be part of the family.
- I see.

1215
01:31:49,875 --> 01:31:54,296
-我知道了
-乖乖跟我做朋友吧
The most sensible thing for you to do
is to be friends with me.

1216
01:31:54,505 --> 01:31:57,216
我愿为你做一切事情
I can do a lot for you, Charlie,
for all of you.

1217
01:31:57,425 --> 01:32:01,387
不我们不要你的帮助
No, not you.
We don't want anything from you.

1218
01:32:01,595 --> 01:32:06,142
-我真希望向妈妈揭穿你
-我知道你想什麽
- I wish I'd told my mother about you.
- I know what you've been thinking.

1219
01:32:06,350 --> 01:32:10,021
你知道她会怎样吗?
她感受如何?
How would your mother have felt?
What would it do to her now?

1220
01:32:10,229 --> 01:32:13,399
你爸爸呢?
他在银行的差事呢?
How about your father?
His job at the bank?

1221
01:32:13,607 --> 01:32:16,277
如果这一切都没有了
你又怎麽样?
What would become of all of you
if everything came out?

1222
01:32:16,444 --> 01:32:19,780
你不用害怕
我不能告诉他们
You needn't be afraid. I can't tell them.

1223
01:32:19,989 --> 01:32:24,618
我才不怕呢
你能向谁说?谁相信你?
But I'm not afraid. What would you tell?
Who'd believe you?

1224
01:32:24,827 --> 01:32:26,954
你脑子里都是想著华尔兹
A waltz runs through your head.

1225
01:32:27,163 --> 01:32:31,375
你从戒指上的刻字
联想到报纸的新闻
You don't like the initials on a ring and
connect it up with a newspaper clipping.

1226
01:32:31,584 --> 01:32:34,045
-你甚至连戒指也丢了
Now, you haven't even got the ring.
I don't know what became of it.

1227
01:32:34,253 --> 01:32:37,131
-你拿了
我?
- You have it.
- I?

1228
01:32:37,340 --> 01:32:39,383
我送给你了
I gave it to you.

1229
01:32:40,926 --> 01:32:46,015
我不要你在这
不要你碰我妈妈
I don't want you here, Uncle Charlie.
I don't want you to touch my mother.

1230
01:32:46,223 --> 01:32:51,228
快走--我警告过你
不然我会亲手杀了你
So go away, I'm warning you.
Go away, or I'll kill you myself.

1231
01:32:51,437 --> 01:32:53,397
看见了吗?
这就是我对你的感觉
See? That's the way I feel about you.

1232
01:33:20,591 --> 01:33:23,052
-给你祖
-噢香水
- Here you are, Joe.
- Oh, perfume.

1233
01:33:23,260 --> 01:33:27,348
-清新芬芳的熏衣草
-我知道
- Just the fresh, clean smell of lavender.
- Yeah, I know.

1234
01:33:27,556 --> 01:33:29,392
-你们都那麽英伟
You look very handsome, both of you.

1235
01:33:29,600 --> 01:33:33,688
-我真为你们感到自豪
-艾玛你也很迷人
- I'm proud of the two men in my family.
- Emmy, you're a dream.

1236
01:33:33,896 --> 01:33:36,440
-别在孩子们说这话
It's a pity the children
have to sit on our laps.

1237
01:33:36,649 --> 01:33:39,902
这裤子有点麻烦
It's going to be a tight squeeze.
It won't do my pants any good.

1238
01:33:40,111 --> 01:33:43,614
<i>-祖我想你来开车
-我们这样分配
- Joe, I wish you could drive.
- We do it this way.</i>

1239
01:33:43,823 --> 01:33:47,368
<i>-查莉你坐--
-查理叔叔可以跟爸爸坐後面...
- Charles, you'll sit -
- He can sit in the back with Dad.</i>

1240
01:33:47,576 --> 01:33:49,829
-孩子们坐在旁边
-不可以
The children can fit in beside them.

1241
01:33:50,037 --> 01:33:51,789
你们都上出租车...
Nonsense. I'm getting a cab.
You all go in the taxi.

1242
01:33:51,998 --> 01:33:55,793
<i>-查莉和我开车
-不查理叔叔你坐出租车
- Charlie and I'll go in the car.
- No, Uncle Charlie, you go in the taxi.</i>

1243
01:33:56,002 --> 01:33:57,211
我要坐出租车!
I want to ride in the taxi!

1244
01:33:57,420 --> 01:33:59,672
当然可以
就这麽定吧
Course you do. So it's all arranged.

1245
01:33:59,880 --> 01:34:03,801
-查莉去车房把车开出来
-我想全家人坐车
- Charlie, run out and get the car.
- I'd rather drive the family.

1246
01:34:04,010 --> 01:34:09,181
我想你在途中听听我演讲
给点意见
I want you to hear my speech
on the way. You're my severest critic.

1247
01:34:09,390 --> 01:34:13,936
<i>安妮
打电话叫辆出租车来
Anyway, we need a taxi.
Ann, go call Mr Abercrombie.</i>

1248
01:34:14,145 --> 01:34:16,605
<i>妈妈!
Mother!</i>

1249
01:34:17,690 --> 01:34:22,111
妈妈带上我
爸爸坐出租车也可以!
Mother, please ride with me.
Father can take the children. Please!

1250
01:35:10,910 --> 01:35:15,164
<i>我肯定是全场
穿得最糟糕的人
Bet I'll be the only man outside
of Charles fool enough to dress up.</i>

1251
01:35:15,373 --> 01:35:19,502
<i>不会了你穿得很体面
Then you'll be the only other on e
to be correct. You look distinguished.</i>

1252
01:35:19,710 --> 01:35:22,046
查理你准备好了吗?
祖你去哪?
Charles, are you all ready? Joe, are you?

1253
01:35:22,254 --> 01:35:24,674
等等!
我把外套带上
Wait a minute!
I've got to get my overcoat.

1254
01:35:24,882 --> 01:35:26,926
噢亲爱的快点!
Please, dear. Hurry!

1255
01:35:27,134 --> 01:35:30,221
别急他们没见到
我是不会开始的
Take your time, Emmy.
They can't start till I get there.

1256
01:35:30,429 --> 01:35:32,515
这里有点冷
It's getting chilly in here.

1257
01:35:32,723 --> 01:35:35,017
<i>这里是圣罗莎
KSRO, Santa Rosa,</i>

1258
01:35:35,226 --> 01:35:38,479
<i>加州的新闻联播
with studios in Vallejo
and Santa Rosa, California.</i>

1259
01:35:38,688 --> 01:35:41,357
放点音乐吧
May as well have a little music
while we wait.

1260
01:35:41,565 --> 01:35:44,902
<i>俄勒冈州警察局
把研究范围缩小
Oregon State Police pressed theirsearch
today for five -</i>

1261
01:35:45,111 --> 01:35:48,030
<i>噢!一定要那麽大声吗?
Oh! Does it have to be so loud?</i>

1262
01:35:48,239 --> 01:35:50,074
把低音听清楚点
Gets the lower tones better.

1263
01:35:50,282 --> 01:35:54,578
<i>我喜欢大声点!
太小声我听不到!
I likeit loud! If the music's too soft,
I can't tell what they're playing.</i>

1264
01:35:54,787 --> 01:35:56,998
如果我有一支乐队
肯定要组成87人
If I have a band,
I'm a-least have 87 men.

1265
01:35:57,206 --> 01:36:00,084
救命!有人被困在车房
Help, everybody!
Somebody's caught in the garage.

1266
01:36:00,292 --> 01:36:03,254
那里令人窒息!
那门开不了
They're suffocating!
There's something wrong with the door.

1267
01:36:03,462 --> 01:36:05,381
祖!
Joe!

1268
01:36:29,405 --> 01:36:31,741
让我来抱她
I'll take her. I've got her.

1269
01:36:35,161 --> 01:36:38,414
祖从我衣柜里
拿瓶酒来快点
Joe, there's some whisky on my bureau.
Get it quick.

1270
01:36:38,622 --> 01:36:41,208
-查莉查莉
-查莉?
- Charlie. Charlie. Dear Charlie.
- Charlie?

1271
01:36:41,417 --> 01:36:44,378
艾玛擦擦她的腿
罗杰给她扇凉
Emmy, rub her feet.
Roger, run get something to fan her with.

1272
01:36:44,587 --> 01:36:46,922
查莉!
Charlie!

1273
01:36:47,131 --> 01:36:49,633
<i>安妮不要这样
Ann, don't, dear.</i>

1274
01:36:49,842 --> 01:36:53,095
查莉?查莉
你想说什麽?
Charlie? What are you trying to say?

1275
01:36:57,892 --> 01:36:59,935
走开
Go away.

1276
01:37:00,144 --> 01:37:01,979
<i>走开
Go away.</i>

1277
01:37:03,314 --> 01:37:05,274
<i>艾玛她需要你
Emmy, she wants you.</i>

1278
01:37:05,483 --> 01:37:10,071
我在这
亲爱的妈妈在这
I'm here, darling. Here's mother.
That's right, my baby.

1279
01:37:10,279 --> 01:37:14,075
没事了
你真勇敢来...
That's right, my brave little girl. Here.

1280
01:37:14,283 --> 01:37:16,619
-喝一口
-不--我没事
- Take a little sip of this.
- No, I'm all right.

1281
01:37:16,827 --> 01:37:21,540
-祖叫菲利医生来
-我没事只想站起来
- Joe, call Dr Phillips.
- No, I'm all right. I just want to get up.

1282
01:37:21,749 --> 01:37:25,670
查莉你很走运
有人把车开著
You had a wonderful escape. Someone
must have left the motor running.

1283
01:37:25,878 --> 01:37:29,382
-我找不到钥匙关上它
-我进去时找到了
- I couldn't find the key to turn it off.
- The key was there when I went in.

1284
01:37:29,590 --> 01:37:31,759
幸亏我路过
Lucky thing I passed by.

1285
01:37:31,967 --> 01:37:35,471
她差点没命
全靠你知道该怎麽做
She might have died. You saved her.
You knew just what to do.

1286
01:37:35,680 --> 01:37:39,850
-我也不知道怎会经过
-把演讲取消吧
- Don't know how I happened across her.
- We'll put the lecture off.

1287
01:37:40,059 --> 01:37:44,522
不你们都快去车来了
Oh, yes, there is. I want you all to go.
There's the cab now.

1288
01:37:44,730 --> 01:37:47,400
噢不行我要在这
Oh, I couldn't. I just couldn't go.

1289
01:37:47,608 --> 01:37:50,861
谁在车房发现我?
Wh-Who found me in the garage?

1290
01:37:51,070 --> 01:37:53,322
<i>贺博听到你在拍门
Herb heard you beating on the door.</i>

1291
01:37:53,531 --> 01:37:57,493
<i>我在後院经过
听到拍门声
I was coming across the backyard
and I heard gaspin' and bangin'.</i>

1292
01:37:57,702 --> 01:38:00,663
我就知道里面肯定有人在
I figured there must be
a human bein' in there.

1293
01:38:00,871 --> 01:38:02,999
<i>-贺博真聪明
-真幸运
- Quick thinking, Herb.
- Lucky thing.</i>

1294
01:38:03,207 --> 01:38:05,584
贺博你刚好
经过救了我
I'm glad you happened
to be going by, Herb.

1295
01:38:05,793 --> 01:38:08,087
<i>来妈妈
Come on, Mother.</i>

1296
01:38:08,295 --> 01:38:10,047
我-我想陪你
I- I want to stay with you.

1297
01:38:10,256 --> 01:38:14,844
我不想演讲了
一想到查莉有危险
I don't feel like making a speech now,
when I think what might have happened.

1298
01:38:15,052 --> 01:38:18,973
我没事
坐下来歇会儿就行了
I'm all right. I just want to sit
on the porch a while and get the air.

1299
01:38:19,181 --> 01:38:20,975
不亲爱的让我陪你
No, darling, I won't hear of it.

1300
01:38:21,183 --> 01:38:26,188
真的没事
我在家准备晚会了
I'm alright, really. I'd rather stay home
and get things ready for the party.

1301
01:38:26,397 --> 01:38:28,899
亲爱的让我留下来
Darling, I want to stay with you.

1302
01:38:34,405 --> 01:38:37,742
贺博你带罗杰好吗?
安妮跟我们坐
Herb, will you take Roger?
Ann, you come with us.

1303
01:38:40,036 --> 01:38:45,499
真奇怪
首先是楼梯有意外--
I just don't understand it.
First the stairs and...

1304
01:39:04,643 --> 01:39:06,937
格翰先生不在?
Mr Graham isn't there?

1305
01:39:09,148 --> 01:39:12,276
是弗雷斯诺的
史都华旅馆吗?
This is the Hotel Stewart in Fresno,
isn't it?

1306
01:39:12,485 --> 01:39:14,904
你没见过他?
And you don't expect him?

1307
01:39:15,112 --> 01:39:17,198
那好了谢谢你
I see. Thank you.

1308
01:39:18,783 --> 01:39:22,745
他不在?
谢谢再见
He isn't there?
Thank you very much. Goodbye.

1309
01:39:23,454 --> 01:39:26,040
你能告诉我怎样找到他吗?
Can you tell me where I can reach him?

1310
01:39:26,248 --> 01:39:30,419
我已经用他留下的地址找他
I've already tried to get him
at the address he gave me in Fresno.

1311
01:39:31,921 --> 01:39:33,964
谢谢
Thank you.

1312
01:40:12,670 --> 01:40:14,463
妈妈我能吃三文治吗?
Mom, may we have some sandwiches?

1313
01:40:14,672 --> 01:40:18,509
不要在客厅拿东西吃
去厨房
Don't take anything from the dining room.
Go in the kitchen.

1314
01:40:18,718 --> 01:40:21,929
<i>让我来拿大衣--
Please go. And just leave your coats...</i>

1315
01:40:23,264 --> 01:40:25,558
<i>祖你来招呼大家吧?
Joe, dear,
will you take care of everyone?</i>

1316
01:40:25,766 --> 01:40:27,268
<i>查莉!
Charlie!</i>

1317
01:40:27,476 --> 01:40:29,270
我下来了
I'll be right down.

1318
01:40:29,478 --> 01:40:32,523
<i>啊...现在...
Well... now... hm.</i>

1319
01:40:35,067 --> 01:40:40,031
奥克里先生
我还想香槟只在打仗时喝
Now, Mr Oakley. I thought champagne
was only for battleships!

1320
01:40:40,239 --> 01:40:45,870
我和妻子都不要了
你们喝吧
None for me, nor I'm sure, for my wife.
But we hope you'll all forget we're here.

1321
01:40:46,078 --> 01:40:49,248
让我们来乾杯--
查莉还没下来吗?
I'd like to propose a toast to...
Isn't Charlie coming down?

1322
01:40:49,457 --> 01:40:52,335
她就下来了波特太太
She'll be down in a moment.
Mrs Potter.

1323
01:40:52,543 --> 01:40:57,298
别吃那个
我弄马铃薯仅为了调味
Not that one. Why do I make tomato?
They always soak through the bread.

1324
01:40:57,506 --> 01:41:02,219
试这个有小麦面包
奶油和辣椒
Try one of these. It's whole wheat bread
and cream cheese. Paprika makes it pink.

1325
01:41:02,428 --> 01:41:04,764
-格林先生
-格林太太你呢?
- Mr Greene.
- Mrs Greene, what would you like?

1326
01:41:04,972 --> 01:41:06,640
谢谢
Thank you.

1327
01:41:06,849 --> 01:41:09,727
-我也要乾杯
-艾玛
- I think I'd like to propose a toast, too.
- Emmy.

1328
01:41:09,935 --> 01:41:15,107
为我们的访客
近年来最好的演讲者
To our distinguished visitor, who made
the best speech heard in town for years.

1329
01:41:15,316 --> 01:41:18,444
为奥克里先生乾杯
To that very good fellow, Mr Oakley.

1330
01:41:18,652 --> 01:41:21,155
-贺比
-谢谢
- Herbie.
- Thank you.

1331
01:41:21,364 --> 01:41:23,324
<i>我们没有什麽
美国的演讲者
We don ' t get many American speakers.</i>

1332
01:41:23,532 --> 01:41:25,284
<i>也许外来的才是最好的
Seems like foreigners
make the best talkers.</i>

1333
01:41:28,496 --> 01:41:31,999
啊她来了我们来乾杯
Ah, here she is. Now for my toast.

1334
01:41:40,299 --> 01:41:42,343
查莉...
Charlie...

1335
01:41:44,136 --> 01:41:46,430
你来得正好
You're just in time for a farewell toast.

1336
01:41:46,639 --> 01:41:51,644
我不得不宣布
明天我会离开这
I hate to break the news to you like this,
but tomorrow I must leave Santa Rosa.

1337
01:41:51,852 --> 01:41:54,980
-暂时离开
-真巧合
- Not forever.
- If that isn't the strangest coincidence.

1338
01:41:55,189 --> 01:41:57,733
<i>-我明天准备去三藩市
-查理
- I'm off to San Francisco.
- Charles?</i>

1339
01:41:59,443 --> 01:42:02,279
噢艾玛
我也不想打扰大家的雅兴
Oh, Emmy darling,
I didn't mean to spoil your fun tonight.

1340
01:42:02,488 --> 01:42:06,283
我收到通知
明早\'要赶火车
I got a letter today.
I have to catch the early morning train.

1341
01:42:07,243 --> 01:42:09,286
艾玛我会想念你
I'll miss you, Emmy.

1342
01:42:12,999 --> 01:42:17,253
我觉得这个小镇的人...
But I want you all to know
I'll always think of this lovely town...

1343
01:42:18,546 --> 01:42:21,465
<i>都很热情好客...
as a place of hospitality
and kindness...</i>

1344
01:42:22,633 --> 01:42:25,594
<i>令我有家的温暖...家
and homes... homes.</i>

1345
01:42:25,803 --> 01:42:30,558
-查理我不想你走
-艾玛我会回来的
- But I can't bear it if you go, Charles.
- Oh, Emmy, I'll be back.

1346
01:42:30,766 --> 01:42:36,397
<i>我还有建造
孩子们的医院呢
I've arranged with Dr Phillips
for our little memorial for the children.</i>

1347
01:42:37,565 --> 01:42:40,568
不是你要做什麽
It isn't any of the things you've done.

1348
01:42:41,610 --> 01:42:47,116
只是我们好不容易才一起!
It's just the idea
that we were together again. I'm sorry.

1349
01:42:47,325 --> 01:42:51,287
<i>我们从小相依为命
But you see,
we were so close growing up.</i>

1350
01:42:51,495 --> 01:42:54,999
後来查理走了我嫁人了--
And then Charles went away,
and I got married, and...

1351
01:42:56,334 --> 01:42:58,794
<i>大家都知道後来怎样
Then, you know how it is.</i>

1352
01:42:59,920 --> 01:43:03,215
<i>身为人妻
就变得很健忘了--
You sort of forget you're you.
You're your husband's wife...</i>

1353
01:43:06,093 --> 01:43:09,180
我们把你看成
是这里的一分子
We'll be looking for you. We feel
you're one of us, don't we, Margaret?

1354
01:43:09,388 --> 01:43:12,975
是啊你也是俱乐部的成员
Indeed. I want to thank you
on behalf of our club.

1355
01:43:13,184 --> 01:43:15,186
很感谢你给医院的礼物
And bless you
for your gift to our hospital.

1356
01:43:15,394 --> 01:43:18,981
-孩子们以後会感激你的
-谢谢你
- The children will bless you, too.
- Thank you, sir.

1357
01:43:19,190 --> 01:43:22,693
<i>打扰了但我
我听到火车来了
Excuse me, sir,
but I-I can hear the train coming now.</i>

1358
01:43:22,902 --> 01:43:24,320
不好意思
Excuse me.

1359
01:43:36,290 --> 01:43:38,376
查理上车吧
Better get aboard, Charles.

1360
01:43:38,584 --> 01:43:43,255
大家後会有期
罗杰安妮跟我来
Alright. Goodbye, everybody.
Roger, Ann, come see the train.

1361
01:43:43,464 --> 01:43:46,258
查莉来啊
Come on, Charlie.
You can see they get off.

1362
01:43:46,467 --> 01:43:48,302
好吧
Alright.

1363
01:43:48,511 --> 01:43:50,721
<i>我想看看包厢
I want to see the rooms,
the private ones.</i>

1364
01:43:50,930 --> 01:43:54,892
我见过卧铺
还睡过上层呢
I've seen berths. I've slept in two uppers
and one lower with papa.

1365
01:43:55,101 --> 01:43:57,853
-再见祖
-再见查理
- Goodbye, Joe.
- Goodbye, Charles.

1366
01:43:58,062 --> 01:44:01,315
-再见艾玛
-再见记得写信!
- Goodbye, Emmy.
- Goodbye. And don't forget to write!

1367
01:44:01,524 --> 01:44:05,569
我会的你也要啊
I will. You write too.
I'll send you my address.

1368
01:44:10,783 --> 01:44:12,827
再见
Goodbye.

1369
01:44:16,122 --> 01:44:18,457
不要在座位上跳来跳去
Don't jump on the seats, Roger.

1370
01:44:20,418 --> 01:44:22,628
罗杰听到吗?
Roger, what did I tell you?

1371
01:44:26,132 --> 01:44:29,885
还有一个箱子
能帮我拿来吗?
Porter, there's one more bag
in the other car. Will you get it, please?

1372
01:44:30,094 --> 01:44:33,305
查莉车要开了
我可不想留下来
Charlie, the train's going to start.
I don't want to get carried away.

1373
01:44:33,514 --> 01:44:36,267
太迟了!
我要快点下去!
Maybe it's too late!
Maybe I'll have to go along!

1374
01:44:36,475 --> 01:44:38,602
我们就跟著来
There's plenty of time.
You run along, we'll follow.

1375
01:44:38,811 --> 01:44:40,438
查莉
Charlie.

1376
01:44:41,272 --> 01:44:43,315
等等
Just a minute.

1377
01:44:44,608 --> 01:44:48,696
我想告诉你
让我离开是明智的
I want you to know
I think you were right to make me leave.

1378
01:44:49,780 --> 01:44:53,367
为你妈妈，对大家都好
It's best for your mother,
best for all of us.

1379
01:44:54,660 --> 01:44:57,663
你看到昨晚她的反应了
You saw what happened
to her last night.

1380
01:44:57,872 --> 01:45:02,585
她不够坚强
我想她不能承受这打击
She's not very strong, you know.
I don't think she could stand the shock.

1381
01:45:02,793 --> 01:45:05,963
-记得当她还是个孩子
-火车开了!
- I remember once, when she was little -
- The train's moving!

1382
01:45:06,172 --> 01:45:09,467
听着查莉，忘记我的过去
Listen, Charlie.
I want you to forget all about me.

1383
01:45:09,675 --> 01:45:12,428
忘记所有
Forget that I ever came to Santa Rosa.

1384
01:45:13,846 --> 01:45:15,514
你的手!
Your hands!

1385
01:45:17,641 --> 01:45:20,644
查理叔叔
放手!让我走!
Let me go, Uncle Charlie! Let me go!

1386
01:45:24,190 --> 01:45:26,400
查莉我不想的
I've got to do this, Charlie...

1387
01:45:26,609 --> 01:45:29,362
但你知道的太多了
so long as you know
what you do about me.

1388
01:45:41,165 --> 01:45:43,501
没到时候等车再快点
Not yet, Charlie. Let it get a little faster.

1389
01:45:45,461 --> 01:45:47,004
再快点
Just a little faster.

1390
01:45:47,213 --> 01:45:48,506
快点
Faster.

1391
01:45:48,714 --> 01:45:50,174
现在!
Now!

1392
01:46:15,992 --> 01:46:18,244
<i>圣罗莎失去了一个好儿子
Santa Rosa has gained
and lost a son,</i>

1393
01:46:18,452 --> 01:46:20,913
<i>一个她引以为荣的儿子
a son that she can be proud of.</i>

1394
01:46:21,122 --> 01:46:25,751
<i>勇敢慷慨善良
优秀的人格
Brave, generous, kindly.
With all of the spendid dignity -</i>

1395
01:46:25,960 --> 01:46:28,963
杰克你来了真好
I'm glad you were able to come, Jack.

1396
01:46:29,171 --> 01:46:33,092
我想找人倾诉
I couldn't have faced it
without someone who knew.

1397
01:46:34,677 --> 01:46:38,723
-我知道很多但不能对你说
-我明白
- I did know more. I couldn't tell you.
- I know.

1398
01:46:40,766 --> 01:46:44,228
他认为这世界是很可怕的
He thought the world was a horrible place.

1399
01:46:44,437 --> 01:46:48,232
-他从来没有快乐过
-没有
- He couldn't have been very happy ever.
- No.

1400
01:46:49,984 --> 01:46:54,113
他不相信身边任何人
He didn't trust people.
He seemed to hate them.

1401
01:46:54,321 --> 01:46:56,574
他憎恨这个世界
He hated the whole world.

1402
01:46:58,159 --> 01:47:01,537
他说过，像我们这样的人...
You know, he said that people like us

1403
01:47:01,746 --> 01:47:05,791
不知道外面的世界是怎样
had no idea what the world was really like.

1404
01:47:06,000 --> 01:47:08,919
也不是那麽糟糕
Well, it's not quite as bad as that,

1405
01:47:09,128 --> 01:47:11,922
只是做人要留个心眼
but sometimes it needs a lot of watching.

1406
01:47:12,131 --> 01:47:15,051
有时人也会走向极端
It seems to go crazy every now and then.

1407
01:47:15,259 --> 01:47:17,303
像你的查理叔叔
Like your Uncle Charlie.

1408
01:47:17,511 --> 01:47:21,432
<i>他高尚的灵魂讨人喜欢的性格，永远与我们同在
The beauty of their souls, and characters live on with us forever.</i>

